WEBVTT

1
00:00:57.175 --> 00:01:00.469
These violent delights
have violent ends.

2
00:01:01.430 --> 00:01:05.015
and in their triumph die.
like fire and powder.

3
00:01:06.351 --> 00:01:09.603
which. as they kiss. consume.

4
00:01:44.890 --> 00:01:46.056
Gran?

5
00:02:02.782 --> 00:02:05.075
Edward. don't! She'll see you.

6
00:02:11.082 --> 00:02:12.082
Hmm.

7
00:02:15.754 --> 00:02:16.962
Okay.

8
00:02:27.265 --> 00:02:29.517
Gran. I'd like you to meet...

9
00:02:59.005 --> 00:03:00.881
Happy birthday. Bella.

10
00:03:13.770 --> 00:03:15.312
Happy birthday.

11
00:03:20.151 --> 00:03:21.694
I thought we agreed.
no presents.

12
00:03:21.778 --> 00:03:25.322
Well. the one from me's not
wrapped. so it doesn't count.

13
00:03:29.661 --> 00:03:31.829
That's actually great.
Thanks. Dad.

14
00:03:32.205 --> 00:03:36.083
It goes with this one from
your mom. We coordinated.

15
00:03:36.334 --> 00:03:38.419
Well. she coordinated me.

16
00:03:40.297 --> 00:03:43.757
It's to put your pictures
in from senior year.

17
00:03:45.343 --> 00:03:47.469
Senior year.

18
00:03:48.430 --> 00:03:52.057
How'd you get so old so fast?
I didn't. It's not that old.

19
00:03:52.350 --> 00:03:54.935
I don't know. Is
that a gray hair?

20
00:03:55.604 --> 00:03:57.021
No. No way.

21
00:04:01.192 --> 00:04:02.735
Happy birthday.

22
00:04:02.819 --> 00:04:04.236
That's really funny.

23
00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:08.699
Another missing hiker
brings the total to three presumed dead.

24
00:04:08.783 --> 00:04:10.492
Rangers are searching for
the killer animal...

25
00:04:12.954 --> 00:04:15.748
Situation's a! Critica!

26
00:04:15.832 --> 00:04:19.668
You've got to look
first before you go.

27
00:04:19.753 --> 00:04:21.670
It's Bella. Bella!

28
00:04:22.047 --> 00:04:23.589
Hi.
I'm...

29
00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:27.885
Today's the big day. Bella.

30
00:04:28.803 --> 00:04:30.554
A and J essay due.

31
00:04:30.889 --> 00:04:34.016
Oh. yeah.
Wherefore art thou. Bella?

32
00:04:35.226 --> 00:04:39.021
Let me take a picture of you guys. My
mom wants me to put together. like.

33
00:04:39.105 --> 00:04:40.265
a scrapbook full of memories.

34
00:04:40.315 --> 00:04:41.355
Oh.
Cool. Yeah.

35
00:04:41.399 --> 00:04:42.733
I take them. I'm not in them.

36
00:04:42.817 --> 00:04:44.193
No. no. no. come here.
Well. you are today.

37
00:04:44.277 --> 00:04:45.653
You'll photoshop this if
my nose looks big. right?

38
00:04:45.737 --> 00:04:49.531
Don't worry. I'm in the picture.
No one will be looking at you guys.

39
00:04:49.616 --> 00:04:51.033
That's good.

40
00:04:51.743 --> 00:04:53.786
Oh. good. Cullen's here.

41
00:04:56.790 --> 00:04:58.832
Well. talk to you later.

42
00:05:21.856 --> 00:05:23.524
Happy birthday.
Don't remind me.

43
00:05:23.608 --> 00:05:24.608
Mmm.

44
00:05:26.319 --> 00:05:28.862
Bella. your birth is definitely
something to celebrate.

45
00:05:28.947 --> 00:05:31.657
Yeah. but my aging's not.
Your aging?

46
00:05:33.993 --> 00:05:36.787
I think 18 is a little young
to start worrying about that.

47
00:05:36.871 --> 00:05:38.497
It's one year older than you.

48
00:05:38.581 --> 00:05:41.125
No. it isn't. I'm 109.

49
00:05:41.376 --> 00:05:44.545
Well. maybe I shouldn't be
dating such an old man.

50
00:05:44.629 --> 00:05:48.173
Mmm.
It's gross. I should be thoroughly repulsed.

51
00:05:48.258 --> 00:05:49.258
Uh-huh.

52
00:06:00.019 --> 00:06:02.438
We have to go to class.
Okay.

53
00:06:07.193 --> 00:06:08.736
Wait a second.

54
00:06:09.654 --> 00:06:11.405
Someone wants you.

55
00:06:12.115 --> 00:06:13.991
Bella!
Jacob!

56
00:06:14.534 --> 00:06:15.784
What?

57
00:06:17.537 --> 00:06:19.621
I'll leave you to talk.

58
00:06:23.835 --> 00:06:27.588
Hello. biceps! You know. anabolic
steroids are really bad for you.

59
00:06:28.757 --> 00:06:31.049
Well. I'm just
filling out. Bella.

60
00:06:31.134 --> 00:06:34.553
You know. it wouldn't seem so
drastic if we hung out more.

61
00:06:35.054 --> 00:06:37.931
You should switch schools. You can
come hang out with the palefaces.

62
00:06:38.016 --> 00:06:41.477
I'm all right. I prefer the
rez school's exclusivity.

63
00:06:42.103 --> 00:06:44.563
They let any old riffraff
into this place.

64
00:06:44.647 --> 00:06:46.732
I see. Then why are you slumming it?
Mmm-hmm.

65
00:06:46.816 --> 00:06:49.276
I was just buying a
part for the Rabbit.

66
00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:51.904
You should really come take
a ride when it's done.

67
00:06:51.988 --> 00:06:53.363
Is it fast?

68
00:06:53.490 --> 00:06:54.490
Um.

69
00:06:55.283 --> 00:06:56.366
It's decent.

70
00:06:57.535 --> 00:06:59.828
I'm kidding.
Okay. Good.

71
00:07:00.538 --> 00:07:02.664
Hey. happy birthday.

72
00:07:04.209 --> 00:07:06.376
Your dad told my dad. so...

73
00:07:07.045 --> 00:07:09.004
Yeah. of course he did.

74
00:07:09.547 --> 00:07:12.132
I saw this the other day
and thought of you.

75
00:07:13.718 --> 00:07:15.511
Catches bad dreams.

76
00:07:17.555 --> 00:07:19.556
That's kind of perfect.

77
00:07:21.726 --> 00:07:23.101
Thank you.

78
00:07:23.686 --> 00:07:25.103
No problem.

79
00:07:27.398 --> 00:07:28.482
Good seeing you.
Yeah. I'll see you later.

80
00:07:28.566 --> 00:07:29.691
Bye.

81
00:07:31.152 --> 00:07:34.863
So how come Jacob Black gets to
give you a gift and I don't?

82
00:07:36.032 --> 00:07:38.909
Because I have nothing
to give back to you.

83
00:07:39.577 --> 00:07:42.412
Bella. you give me everything
just by breathing.

84
00:07:44.415 --> 00:07:45.999
See? Thank you.

85
00:07:46.543 --> 00:07:48.669
That's all I want.
Bella!

86
00:07:50.171 --> 00:07:51.547
Happy birthday!
Shh. shh!

87
00:07:55.176 --> 00:07:56.343
I thought I said no presents.

88
00:07:56.427 --> 00:07:58.554
I've already seen you
open it. and guess what.

89
00:07:58.638 --> 00:08:00.055
you love it.

90
00:08:00.139 --> 00:08:02.933
You're gonna wear it tonight.
Our place.

91
00:08:04.686 --> 00:08:07.688
Come on. Please? It'll be fun.

92
00:08:11.317 --> 00:08:13.694
Okay. All right.
Great!

93
00:08:13.778 --> 00:08:15.904
Okay. I'll see you at 7:00.

94
00:08:17.949 --> 00:08:20.909
Jasper. no fair with the
mood control thing.

95
00:08:22.495 --> 00:08:25.080
Sorry. Bella. Happy...

96
00:08:26.416 --> 00:08:27.791
Never mind.

97
00:08:30.086 --> 00:08:33.338
You can't trust vampires.
Trust me.

98
00:08:34.299 --> 00:08:36.383
O my love! My wife!

99
00:08:37.176 --> 00:08:39.344
Death. that hath sucked
the honey of thy breath

100
00:08:39.429 --> 00:08:41.847
hath had no power yet
upon thy beauty.

101
00:08:43.016 --> 00:08:44.892
Thou art not conquered.

102
00:08:46.352 --> 00:08:50.272
Beauty's ensign yet is crimson
in thy lips and in thy cheeks.

103
00:08:51.107 --> 00:08:53.942
And death's pale flag
is not advanced there.

104
00:08:54.027 --> 00:08:55.986
I hate being celebrated.

105
00:08:56.696 --> 00:08:59.615
There are worse tragedies.
I mean. look at Romeo.

106
00:08:59.699 --> 00:09:02.659
Killed his true love out
of sheer stupidity.

107
00:09:04.579 --> 00:09:05.662
Yeah.

108
00:09:06.164 --> 00:09:08.332
Though I do envy him one thing.

109
00:09:10.209 --> 00:09:12.252
Juliet is. like. perfect.

110
00:09:12.337 --> 00:09:15.589
If you like that obviously
beautiful sort of thing.

111
00:09:18.885 --> 00:09:21.845
Not the girl. the suicide.

112
00:09:25.767 --> 00:09:28.018
It's nearly impossible for...

113
00:09:29.479 --> 00:09:32.105
For some people.

114
00:09:34.776 --> 00:09:38.028
For humans. a little poison.

115
00:09:40.114 --> 00:09:42.115
a dagger to the heart.

116
00:09:43.409 --> 00:09:45.994
There's so many
different options.

117
00:09:49.248 --> 00:09:51.166
Why would you say that?

118
00:09:52.460 --> 00:09:54.962
Because I had to
consider it once.

119
00:09:57.173 --> 00:09:59.216
I didn't know if I'd
get to you in time.

120
00:09:59.842 --> 00:10:03.011
I had to come up with
some kind of plan.

121
00:10:04.263 --> 00:10:05.973
What was the plan?

122
00:10:06.057 --> 00:10:09.518
That I'd go to Italy and
provoke the Volturi.

123
00:10:10.353 --> 00:10:12.562
The what?
The Volturi.

124
00:10:12.647 --> 00:10:16.108
Now. who'd like to repeat
the last few lines of iambic pentameter

125
00:10:16.192 --> 00:10:18.735
just to show they were
paying attention?

126
00:10:19.153 --> 00:10:20.570
Mr. Cullen?

127
00:10:23.574 --> 00:10:25.242
Yes. Mr. Berty.

128
00:10:27.954 --> 00:10:31.832
O here will I set up
my everlasting rest

129
00:10:33.835 --> 00:10:38.005
and shake the yoke of inauspicious stars
from this world-wearied flesh.

130
00:10:38.840 --> 00:10:40.716
Eyes. look your last.

131
00:10:41.300 --> 00:10:43.593
Arms. take your last embrace!

132
00:10:44.554 --> 00:10:47.431
And. lips. O you. the
doors of breath.

133
00:10:48.099 --> 00:10:52.436
seal with a righteous kiss a dateless
bargain to engrossing death!

134
00:10:54.689 --> 00:10:56.773
Eyes on the screen. people.

135
00:10:58.443 --> 00:11:00.777
Thus with a kiss I die.

136
00:11:04.115 --> 00:11:07.367
The Volturi are a very
old. very powerful family.

137
00:11:07.952 --> 00:11:11.621
I guess they're the closest
thing to royalty my world has.

138
00:11:12.206 --> 00:11:14.416
Is that Carlisle?
Yeah.

139
00:11:15.626 --> 00:11:17.794
He lived with them
for a few decades.

140
00:11:17.879 --> 00:11:22.466
Described them as very refined. No
respect for human life. of course.

141
00:11:23.426 --> 00:11:26.845
but a respect for the arts
and the sciences. at least.

142
00:11:28.431 --> 00:11:29.931
And the law.

143
00:11:30.933 --> 00:11:32.684
Above all. the law.

144
00:11:35.938 --> 00:11:37.689
Vampires have laws?

145
00:11:39.233 --> 00:11:40.859
Not very many.

146
00:11:42.028 --> 00:11:44.863
And only one that's
regularly enforced.

147
00:11:47.366 --> 00:11:48.825
What is it?

148
00:11:49.911 --> 00:11:52.996
That we keep the existence
of our kind a secret.

149
00:11:53.456 --> 00:11:56.500
We don't make spectacles
of ourselves.

150
00:11:58.377 --> 00:12:00.921
and we don't kill conspicuously.

151
00:12:04.842 --> 00:12:07.302
Unless. of course.
you want to die.

152
00:12:21.776 --> 00:12:23.777
You gotta stop
talking about that.

153
00:12:23.861 --> 00:12:27.656
I can't even think about
someone hurting you.

154
00:12:30.243 --> 00:12:34.329
Bella. the only thing
that can hurt me is you.

155
00:12:36.707 --> 00:12:39.167
And I don't have anything
else to be afraid of.

156
00:12:39.252 --> 00:12:40.335
That's not true.

157
00:12:42.797 --> 00:12:45.549
Victoria? She'll
come for me one day.

158
00:12:46.467 --> 00:12:50.971
Alice will see when she
decides. and we'll be ready.

159
00:12:51.222 --> 00:12:53.140
I could protect you

160
00:12:54.100 --> 00:12:55.892
if you change me.

161
00:12:56.561 --> 00:12:58.979
Bella. you already
do protect me.

162
00:13:00.940 --> 00:13:02.941
You're my only reason

163
00:13:04.569 --> 00:13:06.361
to stay alive.

164
00:13:07.029 --> 00:13:08.864
if that's what I am.

165
00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:13.493
But it's my job to protect you.

166
00:13:17.081 --> 00:13:20.167
From everyone except my sister.

167
00:13:20.251 --> 00:13:23.461
It's time! It's time. It's time.
It's time!

168
00:13:26.340 --> 00:13:28.967
Your lips are nettles.

169
00:13:29.051 --> 00:13:31.094
Your tongue is wine.

170
00:13:31.596 --> 00:13:34.181
You're left as liquid
But your body's pine.

171
00:13:34.265 --> 00:13:35.932
Sorry about all this.

172
00:13:36.017 --> 00:13:38.852
We tried to rein Alice in.
As if that were even possible.

173
00:13:38.936 --> 00:13:41.438
Happy birthday. Bella.
Thanks.

174
00:13:44.400 --> 00:13:47.360
I found it in your bag.
You mind?

175
00:13:48.112 --> 00:13:50.363
Dating an older woman. Hot.

176
00:13:52.575 --> 00:13:54.784
What?
You first. Rosalie.

177
00:13:57.663 --> 00:14:00.749
It's a necklace.
Alice picked it out.

178
00:14:01.167 --> 00:14:02.375
Thanks.

179
00:14:05.129 --> 00:14:06.796
Show me the love.

180
00:14:10.509 --> 00:14:12.510
This one's from Emmett.

181
00:14:14.972 --> 00:14:17.474
Already installed
it in your truck.

182
00:14:17.558 --> 00:14:18.975
Finally a decent sound system

183
00:14:19.060 --> 00:14:21.436
for that piece of...
Hey! Don't hate the truck.

184
00:14:22.647 --> 00:14:24.814
Open Esme and Carlisle's.

185
00:14:26.067 --> 00:14:28.568
Just a little something
to brighten your day.

186
00:14:28.653 --> 00:14:31.655
Yes. you've been looking
kind of pale lately.

187
00:14:36.911 --> 00:14:37.911
Ow.

188
00:14:39.664 --> 00:14:40.997
Paper cut.

189
00:15:05.731 --> 00:15:08.817
Jaz. Jaz. It's okay.
It's just a little

190
00:15:11.195 --> 00:15:12.529
blood.

191
00:15:19.036 --> 00:15:20.954
Get Jasper out of here.

192
00:15:26.711 --> 00:15:29.004
I'm sorry. I can't.

193
00:15:31.299 --> 00:15:34.092
I'll have to stitch
this up in my office.

194
00:15:36.387 --> 00:15:38.013
Check on Jasper.

195
00:15:38.806 --> 00:15:40.326
I'm sure he's very
upset with himself.

196
00:15:40.349 --> 00:15:43.810
and I doubt he'll listen to
anyone but you right now.

197
00:15:43.894 --> 00:15:45.103
Edward.

198
00:15:56.574 --> 00:16:00.076
I never wanted to have a party.
It's not your fault.

199
00:16:02.121 --> 00:16:06.249
Jasper hasn't been away from human
blood as long as the rest of us.

200
00:16:07.001 --> 00:16:08.626
How do you do it?

201
00:16:09.587 --> 00:16:11.755
Years and years of practice.

202
00:16:12.256 --> 00:16:16.134
Did you ever think of just
doing it the easy way?

203
00:16:17.970 --> 00:16:19.054
No.

204
00:16:20.222 --> 00:16:23.641
I knew who I wanted to be.
I wanted to help people.

205
00:16:24.852 --> 00:16:28.146
It brings me happiness. even
if I am damned regardless.

206
00:16:30.649 --> 00:16:31.983
Damned?

207
00:16:32.943 --> 00:16:35.695
Like hell?

208
00:16:42.119 --> 00:16:44.579
Carlisle. you
couldn't be damned.

209
00:16:44.955 --> 00:16:47.248
You couldn't. It's impossible.

210
00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:49.376
Thank you. Bella.

211
00:16:49.460 --> 00:16:53.588
You've always been very
gracious about us.

212
00:16:57.635 --> 00:17:00.929
So that's it? That's why
he won't change me?

213
00:17:03.974 --> 00:17:06.393
Imagine the situation
in reverse. Hmm.

214
00:17:08.479 --> 00:17:10.897
If you believed as Edward does.

215
00:17:12.274 --> 00:17:14.484
could you take away his soul?

216
00:17:37.675 --> 00:17:39.551
You can't protect me

217
00:17:41.679 --> 00:17:43.346
from everything.

218
00:17:43.806 --> 00:17:46.766
At some point. something's
gonna separate us.

219
00:17:48.477 --> 00:17:51.104
It's gonna be an
accident or illness

220
00:17:52.273 --> 00:17:53.690
or old age.

221
00:17:55.443 --> 00:17:59.821
as long as I'm human. And the
only solution is to change me.

222
00:18:02.324 --> 00:18:05.034
That's not a solution.
That's a tragedy.

223
00:18:05.119 --> 00:18:08.746
You're not gonna want me when
I look like a grandmother.

224
00:18:17.840 --> 00:18:22.260
Bella. do you not understand
my feelings for you at all?

225
00:18:25.014 --> 00:18:26.764
Carlisle told me

226
00:18:29.894 --> 00:18:32.020
how you feel about your soul.

227
00:18:33.606 --> 00:18:35.398
I don't believe that.

228
00:18:36.609 --> 00:18:38.735
So don't worry about mine.

229
00:18:39.862 --> 00:18:41.696
You should go inside.

230
00:18:56.420 --> 00:18:58.338
It's still my birthday.

231
00:19:01.967 --> 00:19:03.968
So can I ask one thing?

232
00:19:07.556 --> 00:19:08.765
Kiss me?

233
00:19:40.214 --> 00:19:45.593
I love you.

234
00:20:14.498 --> 00:20:16.708
Up with your turret.

235
00:20:19.003 --> 00:20:22.964
Aren't we just terrified?

236
00:20:34.643 --> 00:20:38.146
Shale. screen your worry.

237
00:20:39.189 --> 00:20:43.192
From what you won't ever find.

238
00:20:52.578 --> 00:21:00.877
Don't let it fool you.

239
00:21:01.545 --> 00:21:03.588
Down.

240
00:21:07.509 --> 00:21:08.718
Hey.

241
00:21:12.598 --> 00:21:15.058
Just come take a walk with me.

242
00:21:38.832 --> 00:21:40.750
We have to leave Forks.

243
00:21:44.046 --> 00:21:45.254
Why?

244
00:21:48.884 --> 00:21:52.345
Carlisle's supposed to be 10
years older than he looks.

245
00:21:52.429 --> 00:21:54.806
and people are
starting to notice.

246
00:21:57.518 --> 00:22:01.479
Okay. I've gotta think of
something to say to Charlie.

247
00:22:13.367 --> 00:22:15.159
When you say we...

248
00:22:19.456 --> 00:22:21.666
I mean my family and myself.

249
00:22:25.838 --> 00:22:29.424
Edward. what happened with
Jasper. it's nothing.

250
00:22:29.758 --> 00:22:32.468
You're right. It was nothing.

251
00:22:35.055 --> 00:22:37.598
nothing but what I
always expected

252
00:22:39.601 --> 00:22:42.812
and nothing compared to
what could have happened.

253
00:22:48.819 --> 00:22:51.654
You just don't belong
in my world. Bella.

254
00:22:56.702 --> 00:22:58.411
I belong with you.

255
00:23:00.164 --> 00:23:02.498
No. You don't.

256
00:23:05.002 --> 00:23:06.461
I'm coming.

257
00:23:07.504 --> 00:23:08.671
Bella.

258
00:23:10.090 --> 00:23:12.425
I don't want you to come.

259
00:23:19.975 --> 00:23:21.726
You don't want me?

260
00:23:27.483 --> 00:23:28.608
No.

261
00:23:32.279 --> 00:23:35.698
That changes things a lot.

262
00:23:37.201 --> 00:23:39.660
But if it's not too much to ask.

263
00:23:41.455 --> 00:23:43.873
can you just promise
me something?

264
00:23:46.293 --> 00:23:48.461
Don't do anything reckless.

265
00:23:51.215 --> 00:23:53.007
For Charlie's sake.

266
00:23:54.426 --> 00:23:57.386
And I'll promise something
to you in return.

267
00:23:57.471 --> 00:24:00.306
This is the last time
you'll ever see me.

268
00:24:00.891 --> 00:24:02.517
I won't come back.

269
00:24:02.851 --> 00:24:06.896
and you can go on with your life
without any interference from me.

270
00:24:07.689 --> 00:24:11.484
It will be like I never
existed. I promise.

271
00:24:14.905 --> 00:24:18.658
If this is about my soul. take
it. I don't want it without you.

272
00:24:18.742 --> 00:24:20.785
It's not about your soul.

273
00:24:23.914 --> 00:24:26.249
You're just not good for me.

274
00:24:27.835 --> 00:24:29.794
Not good enough for you.

275
00:24:31.046 --> 00:24:33.673
I'm just sorry I let
this go on for so long.

276
00:24:35.551 --> 00:24:36.884
Please...

277
00:24:38.428 --> 00:24:39.720
Don't...

278
00:24:45.060 --> 00:24:46.352
Goodbye.

279
00:25:01.994 --> 00:25:22.805
Edward.

280
00:25:25.809 --> 00:25:27.143
Edward!

281
00:25:35.110 --> 00:25:36.319
Edward.

282
00:27:31.935 --> 00:27:34.645
I'm gonna try the
Cullens' place again.

283
00:27:35.355 --> 00:27:38.441
The Cullens left town. Charlie.
Good riddance.

284
00:27:38.525 --> 00:27:40.234
Where'd they go?

285
00:27:41.236 --> 00:27:43.112
We'll find her. Charlie.

286
00:27:43.196 --> 00:27:45.531
Thanks. Harry.
Charlie!

287
00:27:45.782 --> 00:27:46.907
Hey.

288
00:27:50.162 --> 00:27:51.787
She's all right.

289
00:27:52.622 --> 00:27:56.125
I got her. Thank you. Sam.

290
00:28:37.584 --> 00:28:50.888
There's a possibility.

291
00:28:53.767 --> 00:28:57.353
All that I had.

292
00:28:57.437 --> 00:29:01.023
Was all I'm gonna get.

293
00:29:06.029 --> 00:29:09.365
Alice. you've disappeared.

294
00:29:11.993 --> 00:29:13.953
like everything else.

295
00:29:15.205 --> 00:29:17.915
Now who else can I talk to?
I'm lost.

296
00:29:25.006 --> 00:29:26.632
When you left.

297
00:29:28.552 --> 00:29:30.219
and he left.

298
00:29:32.430 --> 00:29:34.807
you took everything with you.

299
00:29:36.893 --> 00:29:39.937
But the absence of him
is everywhere I look.

300
00:29:47.320 --> 00:29:50.823
It's like a huge hole has been
punched through my chest.

301
00:29:56.454 --> 00:29:57.580
Bella.

302
00:30:13.763 --> 00:30:15.723
But in a way I'm glad.

303
00:30:16.349 --> 00:30:19.351
The pain is my only
reminder that he was real.

304
00:30:19.561 --> 00:30:21.103
that you all were.

305
00:30:29.905 --> 00:30:32.031
All right. That's it.

306
00:30:34.784 --> 00:30:35.910
What?

307
00:30:36.328 --> 00:30:39.622
You're going to Jacksonville
to live with your mother.

308
00:30:41.958 --> 00:30:43.918
I'm not leaving Forks.

309
00:30:45.295 --> 00:30:49.089
Bells. he's not coming back.

310
00:30:52.177 --> 00:30:53.427
I know.

311
00:30:54.638 --> 00:30:57.473
It's just not normal.
this behavior.

312
00:30:58.141 --> 00:31:01.977
Quite frankly. it's scaring the
hell out of me and your mother.

313
00:31:03.647 --> 00:31:05.981
Baby. I don't want you to leave.

314
00:31:06.316 --> 00:31:11.070
I don't. but just go. Go to
Jacksonville. Make some new friends.

315
00:31:11.154 --> 00:31:12.821
I like my old friends.

316
00:31:12.906 --> 00:31:15.658
Well. you never see them anymore.
I do.

317
00:31:18.370 --> 00:31:23.415
I'm gonna go shopping
tomorrow with Jessica.

318
00:31:25.293 --> 00:31:27.419
You hate shopping.
I...

319
00:31:29.172 --> 00:31:31.298
I need a girls' night out.

320
00:31:34.135 --> 00:31:36.929
All right. Girls' night.

321
00:31:38.348 --> 00:31:39.682
Shopping.

322
00:31:40.475 --> 00:31:44.186
I like it. Go buy some stuff.

323
00:31:52.529 --> 00:31:54.530
Hi. Jessica. it's Bella.

324
00:31:55.782 --> 00:31:57.658
Yeah. Bella Swan.

325
00:32:02.706 --> 00:32:04.123
I don't know why you want to
sit through

326
00:32:04.207 --> 00:32:07.459
all those zombies eating people
and no hot guys kissing anybody.

327
00:32:07.544 --> 00:32:11.088
It's gross. Like... And why are there
that many zombie movies anyway?

328
00:32:11.172 --> 00:32:13.757
'Cause if it's supposed to. like.
draw a parallel about leprosy.

329
00:32:13.842 --> 00:32:16.802
my cousin had leprosy.
It's not funny. you know?

330
00:32:16.886 --> 00:32:19.805
And. like. is it supposed to
be a metaphor for consumerism?

331
00:32:19.889 --> 00:32:22.057
Because don't be so pleased
with your own. like.

332
00:32:22.142 --> 00:32:24.768
self-referential cleverness. you know?

333
00:32:24.853 --> 00:32:28.314
Like. some girls like to shop.
Not all girls. apparently.

334
00:32:28.398 --> 00:32:31.400
Although I was surprised you
even called at all. You know?

335
00:32:31.484 --> 00:32:34.611
Like. your depression thing. I get
it. I'm totally. totally worried.

336
00:32:34.696 --> 00:32:35.696
But after a while it's like.

337
00:32:35.780 --> 00:32:37.281
you're still bumming...
You want a ride. girls?

338
00:32:37.365 --> 00:32:39.325
And I'm going through stuff. too.
You know? Like Mike deciding

339
00:32:39.409 --> 00:32:40.530
he just wants to be friends.

340
00:32:40.577 --> 00:32:41.535
What's up? Look what we found.

341
00:32:41.619 --> 00:32:42.828
It's hard. you know?

342
00:32:42.912 --> 00:32:44.204
Like. and since when
does just friends...

343
00:32:44.289 --> 00:32:45.831
What's up guys?
Look what we found.

344
00:32:45.915 --> 00:32:47.958
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
Hey. where you going?

345
00:32:56.051 --> 00:32:57.051
Keep walking.

346
00:32:59.137 --> 00:33:00.804
This is dangerous.

347
00:33:10.231 --> 00:33:12.941
Dude. come on.
Come here for a sec!

348
00:33:17.030 --> 00:33:19.114
I think I know those guys.

349
00:33:19.949 --> 00:33:22.034
We got beer! We got bikes!

350
00:33:22.702 --> 00:33:25.204
Well. they seem great.
Can we go?

351
00:33:26.122 --> 00:33:28.457
I'm just gonna see something.

352
00:33:29.542 --> 00:33:30.959
Hey. girlie!

353
00:33:35.382 --> 00:33:38.092
All right. all right.
We got a taker.

354
00:33:38.802 --> 00:33:40.219
Turn around.

355
00:33:54.984 --> 00:33:57.277
Shut up!
You shut up!

356
00:34:03.618 --> 00:34:04.785
I'm sorry. I thought you
were somebody else.

357
00:34:04.869 --> 00:34:07.704
No. that's cool. I'll be whoever
you want me to be. honey.

358
00:34:07.789 --> 00:34:10.457
So. what do you say?

359
00:34:15.004 --> 00:34:17.589
You promised me.
nothing reckless.

360
00:34:21.511 --> 00:34:24.763
You promised it would be
as if you never existed.

361
00:34:30.270 --> 00:34:33.021
You lied.
You say something. babe?

362
00:34:33.106 --> 00:34:34.606
You know what? Never mind.

363
00:34:51.749 --> 00:34:54.376
Stop! Stop. stop. stop!

364
00:35:04.387 --> 00:35:07.306
Hey. what the hell's
wrong with you?

365
00:35:07.390 --> 00:35:09.057
Just curious.

366
00:35:10.560 --> 00:35:13.479
I thought that I saw something.
You... Oh.

367
00:35:13.897 --> 00:35:17.191
You're insane. actually.
Or suicidal.

368
00:35:17.692 --> 00:35:20.277
That homeboy could've
been a psycho.

369
00:35:20.820 --> 00:35:24.740
I was about to end up in an FBI
interview room like some lame TV show.

370
00:35:25.033 --> 00:35:27.075
God. that was such a rush.

371
00:35:28.786 --> 00:35:31.330
Awesome. So you're an
adrenaline junkie now?

372
00:35:31.414 --> 00:35:32.664
That's cool. You can
go bungee jumping.

373
00:35:32.749 --> 00:35:36.001
You don't get on the back of
some random loser's motorcycle.

374
00:35:36.085 --> 00:35:37.252
Crazy.

375
00:35:41.758 --> 00:35:44.426
Alice. I saw him.

376
00:35:46.513 --> 00:35:49.348
Maybe I'm crazy now.
I guess that's okay.

377
00:35:51.476 --> 00:35:54.728
If a rush of danger is
what it takes to see him.

378
00:35:54.812 --> 00:35:57.064
then that's what I'll find.

379
00:36:01.152 --> 00:36:02.319
Bella!

380
00:36:03.404 --> 00:36:05.489
Where the hell have
you been. loca?

381
00:36:09.536 --> 00:36:11.995
I brought you something.

382
00:36:12.664 --> 00:36:15.290
Okay.
It's a little crazy.

383
00:36:20.338 --> 00:36:21.421
Wow.

384
00:36:21.798 --> 00:36:24.007
Scrap metal. You shouldn't have.

385
00:36:24.092 --> 00:36:26.301
I saved it from the junkyard.

386
00:36:28.555 --> 00:36:32.432
I think they'll probably cost
more to fix than they're worth.

387
00:36:32.684 --> 00:36:34.935
but then I thought that if
I had a mechanic friend

388
00:36:35.019 --> 00:36:36.270
to help me out then...
Ah!

389
00:36:36.354 --> 00:36:39.731
Me being the mechanic-type friend?
That's right.

390
00:36:40.900 --> 00:36:43.944
Since when are you into motorcycles?
Since now.

391
00:36:49.325 --> 00:36:53.203
I get it if you think that this
is really stupid and reckless.

392
00:36:53.288 --> 00:36:56.331
Yeah. I mean. it's completely
stupid and reckless.

393
00:36:59.335 --> 00:37:00.961
When do we start?

394
00:37:03.214 --> 00:37:04.214
Um.

395
00:37:05.049 --> 00:37:06.341
Now.

396
00:37:07.176 --> 00:37:09.011
Please?
All right.

397
00:37:11.472 --> 00:37:15.809
Oh. hey. be careful. Those things
are actually really heavy. so...

398
00:37:21.149 --> 00:37:23.400
Jake. you're. like. buff.

399
00:37:23.484 --> 00:37:25.736
How did that happen? You're.
like. 16. I don't get it.

400
00:37:25.820 --> 00:37:29.156
Mmm-hmm. Age is just a number. baby.
What are you. like. 40 now?

401
00:37:33.494 --> 00:37:35.787
It feels like that sometimes.

402
00:37:46.007 --> 00:37:48.717
That song's good.
You don't like it?

403
00:37:49.844 --> 00:37:54.222
I don't really like
music anymore. kind of.

404
00:37:54.891 --> 00:37:57.392
Okay. No more music.

405
00:38:00.563 --> 00:38:02.648
So I was thinking. if we're
gonna do this every day.

406
00:38:02.732 --> 00:38:04.566
and hopefully we will.

407
00:38:04.651 --> 00:38:07.361
we have to. like. fit some
homework in there somewhere.

408
00:38:07.445 --> 00:38:10.489
I don't want Billy thinking that
I'm a bad influence on you.

409
00:38:10.573 --> 00:38:13.700
You? Influence me? Please.

410
00:38:16.079 --> 00:38:18.580
Are you... I'm older than you.

411
00:38:18.665 --> 00:38:22.000
so that makes me the influencer
and you the influence.

412
00:38:22.085 --> 00:38:23.669
No. no. no.

413
00:38:23.753 --> 00:38:27.506
My size and knowledge base
actually makes me older than you

414
00:38:27.590 --> 00:38:30.092
because of your general paleness
and lack of know-how.

415
00:38:30.176 --> 00:38:32.678
I convinced you to build
two-wheeled death machines with me.

416
00:38:32.762 --> 00:38:36.306
Don't you think that makes
you kind of young and naive?

417
00:38:36.391 --> 00:38:38.600
Okay. So where do we stand?

418
00:38:39.602 --> 00:38:42.562
I'm 35. And you might be. like. 32.
Come on.

419
00:38:43.773 --> 00:38:47.359
Yo. Jake. you in there?
It's okay. It's just my boys.

420
00:38:47.443 --> 00:38:50.195
Hey. Jake.
Hey. Guys. this is Bella.

421
00:38:50.279 --> 00:38:52.823
Bella. that's Quil and Embry.
Hi.

422
00:38:53.491 --> 00:38:55.283
I'm Quil Ateara.

423
00:38:57.370 --> 00:38:59.287
So the bike building
story is true.

424
00:38:59.372 --> 00:39:01.456
Oh. yeah. yeah. I taught
him everything he knows.

425
00:39:01.541 --> 00:39:04.334
What about the part where
you're his girlfriend?

426
00:39:04.961 --> 00:39:05.961
Uh...

427
00:39:06.045 --> 00:39:07.879
We're friends. you know.

428
00:39:07.964 --> 00:39:09.589
Burn.
Actually.

429
00:39:09.674 --> 00:39:12.551
remember I said she's
a girl and a friend.

430
00:39:12.635 --> 00:39:14.511
Embry. do you remember him
making that distinction?

431
00:39:14.595 --> 00:39:15.595
Nope.

432
00:39:15.638 --> 00:39:18.140
So you guys have girlfriends?
That's awesome.

433
00:39:19.392 --> 00:39:22.936
Yeah. right. Quil's actually
taking his cousin to prom.

434
00:39:23.563 --> 00:39:24.730
Yeah. that's still a riot.

435
00:39:24.814 --> 00:39:27.774
You want funny. Black?
I'll give you funny.

436
00:39:29.110 --> 00:39:30.402
Jeez.

437
00:39:30.486 --> 00:39:31.820
Hey. that hold's illegal!

438
00:39:31.904 --> 00:39:33.905
I got five bucks on Quil.

439
00:39:34.240 --> 00:39:35.615
You're on.

440
00:39:37.660 --> 00:39:42.122
All of the astronauts
Champagne in plastic cups.

441
00:39:42.206 --> 00:39:46.501
Waiting for the
big hero to show.

442
00:39:46.669 --> 00:39:51.673
Outside the door he stands
His head in his hands.

443
00:39:51.841 --> 00:39:54.926
And his heart in his throat.

444
00:39:55.011 --> 00:39:58.054
What can he tell them now.

445
00:39:58.389 --> 00:39:59.639
Dear Alice.

446
00:39:59.724 --> 00:40:02.100
I wish I had your real address.

447
00:40:02.518 --> 00:40:05.103
I wish I could tell
you about Jake.

448
00:40:05.354 --> 00:40:07.564
He makes me feel better.

449
00:40:08.733 --> 00:40:11.193
I mean. he makes me feel alive.

450
00:40:13.738 --> 00:40:15.864
The hole in my chest.

451
00:40:16.532 --> 00:40:20.994
well. when I'm with Jake.
it's like it's almost healed

452
00:40:22.121 --> 00:40:23.455
for a while.

453
00:40:23.706 --> 00:40:28.043
So. Quil keeps asking to come over. I
think he likes you a little too much.

454
00:40:28.544 --> 00:40:29.544
Oh.

455
00:40:30.421 --> 00:40:34.216
Well. I'm really not into the
whole cougar thing. You know?

456
00:40:36.385 --> 00:40:38.386
What's up with you and age?

457
00:40:38.888 --> 00:40:41.848
I mean. how old was that
Cullen guy. anyway?

458
00:40:44.435 --> 00:40:47.312
But even Jake can't keep
the dreams away.

459
00:40:56.030 --> 00:40:57.697
Hey. hey. hey!

460
00:40:58.407 --> 00:40:59.574
Wake-up. Bella.

461
00:40:59.659 --> 00:41:02.327
You're okay. You're okay.

462
00:41:13.422 --> 00:41:17.843
I thought this thing was starting
to work. but I guess not.

463
00:41:24.225 --> 00:41:26.268
Can I ask you something?

464
00:41:28.271 --> 00:41:30.188
Hanging out with Jacob.

465
00:41:31.107 --> 00:41:34.818
that seems to take your mind
off things a bit. doesn't it?

466
00:41:39.866 --> 00:41:41.616
You know. sometimes

467
00:41:43.536 --> 00:41:46.663
you gotta learn to love
what's good for you.

468
00:41:47.582 --> 00:41:49.416
You know what I mean?

469
00:41:51.919 --> 00:41:53.962
Of course. what do I know?

470
00:41:54.338 --> 00:41:56.631
I'm just a terminal bachelor.

471
00:41:58.926 --> 00:42:00.927
Famous ladies' man.

472
00:42:03.472 --> 00:42:04.598
Okay.

473
00:42:06.475 --> 00:42:08.101
I'm gonna go to bed.

474
00:42:08.811 --> 00:42:09.811
Uh...

475
00:42:10.313 --> 00:42:11.730
I love you.

476
00:42:17.862 --> 00:42:22.407
If I told you I couldn't have fixed
these bikes. what would you have said?

477
00:42:24.827 --> 00:42:27.245
Are you doubting
your mad skills?

478
00:42:27.914 --> 00:42:31.291
No. Definitely not. I
mean. they'll run fine.

479
00:42:32.209 --> 00:42:33.668
It's just.

480
00:42:35.546 --> 00:42:39.382
maybe if I was smart. I would have
dragged out the rebuild a bit.

481
00:42:43.512 --> 00:42:48.516
If you told me you couldn't fix these bikes.
I would say that that's really too bad.

482
00:42:48.601 --> 00:42:52.479
but that we're just gonna have
to find something else to do.

483
00:42:57.652 --> 00:42:59.361
Is that Sam Uley?

484
00:43:00.363 --> 00:43:02.739
Yeah. Him and his cult.

485
00:43:05.618 --> 00:43:07.077
Oh. my God.

486
00:43:10.164 --> 00:43:11.873
Did you see that?

487
00:43:17.630 --> 00:43:21.466
They're not really fighting.
Bella. They're cliff diving.

488
00:43:21.550 --> 00:43:24.052
Scary as hell. but a total rush.

489
00:43:27.348 --> 00:43:30.141
A rush?
Most of us jump from lower down.

490
00:43:30.226 --> 00:43:33.561
We leave the showing off
to Sam and his disciples.

491
00:43:35.773 --> 00:43:39.067
You have some kind of beef
with him or something?

492
00:43:40.236 --> 00:43:41.736
I don't know.

493
00:43:41.821 --> 00:43:44.406
They just think they
run this place.

494
00:43:44.824 --> 00:43:47.701
Embry used to call them
hall monitors on steroids.

495
00:43:47.785 --> 00:43:50.245
Now look at him.
That's Embry?

496
00:43:52.081 --> 00:43:54.416
Yeah.
What happened to him?

497
00:43:54.917 --> 00:43:56.459
He missed some school.

498
00:43:56.544 --> 00:44:00.630
Now all of a sudden. he started following
Sam around like a little puppy.

499
00:44:00.715 --> 00:44:03.550
Same thing happened
with Paul and Jared.

500
00:44:04.010 --> 00:44:06.302
Sam keeps giving me this look.

501
00:44:08.389 --> 00:44:11.099
like he's waiting for
me or something.

502
00:44:12.393 --> 00:44:15.103
It's kind of starting
to freak me out.

503
00:44:15.187 --> 00:44:17.605
Well. you should just avoid him.

504
00:44:19.608 --> 00:44:20.942
I try.

505
00:44:38.085 --> 00:44:39.419
Okay.

506
00:44:42.506 --> 00:44:44.632
You look scared.
I'm not.

507
00:44:46.093 --> 00:44:47.385
All right.

508
00:44:47.470 --> 00:44:49.471
Brake?
That one.

509
00:44:52.808 --> 00:44:54.184
Clutch?

510
00:44:54.268 --> 00:44:55.477
Good.

511
00:44:55.811 --> 00:44:56.936
Gas?

512
00:44:59.440 --> 00:45:00.690
Ready?

513
00:45:01.817 --> 00:45:04.903
Now. slowly release the clutch.

514
00:45:06.906 --> 00:45:08.114
Bella.

515
00:45:11.660 --> 00:45:12.660
Stop.

516
00:45:14.538 --> 00:45:15.538
Whoa!

517
00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:19.584
You all right?

518
00:45:20.878 --> 00:45:22.670
I'm gonna go again.

519
00:45:23.089 --> 00:45:24.255
Okay.

520
00:45:37.853 --> 00:45:38.853
Ah!

521
00:45:40.314 --> 00:45:41.314
Whoa!

522
00:45:43.025 --> 00:45:44.526
Hit the brake!

523
00:45:59.125 --> 00:46:00.125
I wanna go again.

524
00:46:00.209 --> 00:46:01.960
Are you trying to get
yourself killed?

525
00:46:02.044 --> 00:46:04.587
No. I want to go again.
No. Forget it.

526
00:46:05.381 --> 00:46:07.048
No more bikes.

527
00:46:07.967 --> 00:46:09.551
Man. your head.

528
00:46:10.177 --> 00:46:11.177
Ow.

529
00:46:12.596 --> 00:46:14.848
Yeah.
Oh. my God. I'm sorry.

530
00:46:16.058 --> 00:46:18.726
What. you're apologizing
for bleeding?

531
00:46:20.896 --> 00:46:22.689
Yeah. I guess I am.

532
00:46:23.566 --> 00:46:26.442
Well. it's just blood. Bella.
No big deal.

533
00:46:31.740 --> 00:46:32.991
There.

534
00:46:39.582 --> 00:46:41.624
What are you staring at?

535
00:46:45.004 --> 00:46:47.130
You're sort of beautiful.

536
00:46:55.014 --> 00:46:57.348
How hard did you hit your head?

537
00:46:58.809 --> 00:46:59.851
I don't know.

538
00:47:02.229 --> 00:47:03.605
Let's go.

539
00:47:07.067 --> 00:47:08.747
I did see something in the woods.

540
00:47:09.069 --> 00:47:10.445
Totally. Baby. I believe you.

541
00:47:10.529 --> 00:47:12.822
No. he doesn't. He's just
trying to get lucky.

542
00:47:14.241 --> 00:47:18.244
No. okay. It was
jet black and huge.

543
00:47:18.329 --> 00:47:21.164
On all fours. it was still
taller than a person.

544
00:47:21.248 --> 00:47:22.415
A bear. maybe?

545
00:47:22.499 --> 00:47:24.959
Or an alien. You're lucky
you didn't get probed.

546
00:47:26.378 --> 00:47:28.379
Well. I saw it.

547
00:47:29.131 --> 00:47:31.132
You know. you're
not the only one.

548
00:47:31.967 --> 00:47:34.594
My dad's been getting
reports at the station.

549
00:47:34.678 --> 00:47:37.597
Like. five hikers have
been killed by some bear.

550
00:47:37.681 --> 00:47:39.807
But they can't find the bear.

551
00:47:39.892 --> 00:47:40.892
Hmm.

552
00:47:42.978 --> 00:47:45.855
Last time you clowns
doubt my girlfriend.

553
00:47:46.607 --> 00:47:47.607
Um...

554
00:47:49.985 --> 00:47:51.444
So? I mean.

555
00:47:52.279 --> 00:47:53.905
Bella's back?

556
00:47:57.701 --> 00:47:59.285
Yeah. I guess so.

557
00:47:59.370 --> 00:48:01.955
All right. that's...
Well. welcome.

558
00:48:02.957 --> 00:48:06.042
So. listen. now
that you're talking

559
00:48:07.586 --> 00:48:12.215
and eating again. which. you know.
you've got to get that protein in there.

560
00:48:14.343 --> 00:48:18.554
I was just wondering if you
wanted to go see a movie with me.

561
00:48:22.601 --> 00:48:25.228
Yeah. Sure. Yeah. I do.

562
00:48:27.106 --> 00:48:28.356
Cool.

563
00:48:28.440 --> 00:48:30.942
Let me see. we could check out.

564
00:48:31.527 --> 00:48:33.778
Love Spelled Backwards Is Love.

565
00:48:33.862 --> 00:48:36.948
You know. it's a dumb title.
but it's a romantic comedy.

566
00:48:37.032 --> 00:48:39.867
I mean. it's supposed to be pretty...
No. No romance.

567
00:48:43.956 --> 00:48:47.041
How about Face Punch?
Have you heard of that?

568
00:48:47.876 --> 00:48:50.295
I mean. that's an action movie.

569
00:48:50.379 --> 00:48:52.213
Yeah. that's perfect.

570
00:48:53.048 --> 00:48:54.882
Guns. adrenaline.

571
00:48:55.718 --> 00:48:56.968
That's my thing.

572
00:48:57.052 --> 00:48:58.219
Okay.

573
00:48:58.554 --> 00:49:02.890
We should get a bunch of people to go.
Do you guys want to go see Face Punch?

574
00:49:02.975 --> 00:49:04.183
Face Punch. yeah!

575
00:49:04.268 --> 00:49:05.768
Mike. hey. we were
supposed to watch that.

576
00:49:05.853 --> 00:49:07.395
Remember. the trailer's like...

577
00:49:07.479 --> 00:49:09.689
Punch faces.
I remember.

578
00:49:09.773 --> 00:49:12.483
Yeah!
Movie night with Bella.

579
00:49:15.738 --> 00:49:17.572
So Face Punch. huh?

580
00:49:18.240 --> 00:49:20.241
You like action movies?

581
00:49:21.160 --> 00:49:22.660
Not really.

582
00:49:25.622 --> 00:49:28.416
I heard it sucks. Bad.

583
00:49:29.918 --> 00:49:32.795
Are you even old enough
to see this movie?

584
00:49:33.756 --> 00:49:35.506
I mean. you know. without.
like. adult supervision.

585
00:49:35.591 --> 00:49:37.511
Right. yeah. well. she's
buying my ticket for me.

586
00:49:37.593 --> 00:49:39.552
She's buying it. Okay.

587
00:49:40.637 --> 00:49:43.598
Jessica bailed. and Angela
got the stomach flu.

588
00:49:43.682 --> 00:49:45.933
so Eric's taking care of her.

589
00:49:46.935 --> 00:49:49.103
It's just us three.
Great!

590
00:49:50.189 --> 00:49:51.731
Great.
Yeah.

591
00:49:54.902 --> 00:49:56.194
Put your gun down.

592
00:49:56.278 --> 00:49:58.988
Put your gun down
or I'm gonna blow your frickin' head off.

593
00:49:59.073 --> 00:50:01.532
Both of you put both
of your guns down

594
00:50:01.617 --> 00:50:04.327
or I'm gonna blow both of
your frickin' heads off.

595
00:50:05.746 --> 00:50:07.205
All right. forget it.
let's do this!

596
00:50:25.641 --> 00:50:28.142
Okay. I think I'm
gonna throw up.

597
00:50:34.358 --> 00:50:35.650
He's...

598
00:50:36.026 --> 00:50:37.819
What a marshmallow!

599
00:50:38.987 --> 00:50:42.407
You should hold out for someone
with a stronger stomach.

600
00:50:42.491 --> 00:50:45.952
Someone who laughs at the gore
that makes weaker men vomit.

601
00:50:46.036 --> 00:50:47.870
Yeah. I'll keep my
eye open for that.

602
00:50:50.165 --> 00:50:54.502
I feel bad. He probably has
that flu that's going around.

603
00:50:57.840 --> 00:51:00.174
What? I can't hold your hand?

604
00:51:00.259 --> 00:51:02.301
No. of course you can.

605
00:51:05.139 --> 00:51:09.183
I just think it means. you know. something
a little different to you. So...

606
00:51:11.353 --> 00:51:14.772
Okay. well. tell me something.
You like me. right?

607
00:51:19.611 --> 00:51:22.280
And you think I'm
sort of beautiful?

608
00:51:23.365 --> 00:51:26.993
Jacob. please. don't do this.

609
00:51:33.750 --> 00:51:34.876
Why?

610
00:51:38.297 --> 00:51:41.090
Because you're about
to ruin everything.

611
00:51:42.926 --> 00:51:45.553
And I need you.

612
00:51:52.478 --> 00:51:54.937
Well. I've got loads of time.

613
00:51:56.064 --> 00:51:57.982
I'm not gonna give up.

614
00:51:59.109 --> 00:52:01.736
I don't want you to.

615
00:52:03.989 --> 00:52:07.200
but it's just 'cause I don't
want you to go anywhere.

616
00:52:09.745 --> 00:52:11.996
And that's really selfish.

617
00:52:15.501 --> 00:52:18.753
You know. I'm not like a
car that you can fix up.

618
00:52:22.883 --> 00:52:26.928
I'm never gonna run right.
So I should be fair to you.

619
00:52:29.348 --> 00:52:31.599
It's because of him. right?

620
00:52:41.902 --> 00:52:43.110
Look.

621
00:52:44.780 --> 00:52:47.198
I know what he did to you.

622
00:52:48.575 --> 00:52:52.787
But. Bella. I would
never ever do that.

623
00:52:55.499 --> 00:52:58.709
I won't ever hurt you.
I promise.

624
00:53:00.212 --> 00:53:02.129
I won't let you down.

625
00:53:03.090 --> 00:53:04.966
You can count on me.

626
00:53:12.808 --> 00:53:13.808
Well.

627
00:53:19.231 --> 00:53:20.982
I need to go home.

628
00:53:28.115 --> 00:53:30.992
I was feeling sick
before the movie. Okay?

629
00:53:34.204 --> 00:53:35.538
What is your problem?

630
00:53:35.622 --> 00:53:37.873
Right now? You're my problem.

631
00:53:38.542 --> 00:53:41.877
Feeling sick? Maybe you
need to go to the hospital.

632
00:53:43.005 --> 00:53:44.839
You want me to put
you in the hospital?

633
00:53:44.923 --> 00:53:48.259
Jake! Jake. Jake. the movie's
over. What are you doing?

634
00:53:48.677 --> 00:53:51.304
You're really hot.

635
00:53:52.848 --> 00:53:56.142
Like. you feel like you
have a fever. Are you okay?

636
00:53:57.144 --> 00:53:59.437
I don't know what's happening.

637
00:54:01.398 --> 00:54:02.898
I gotta go.

638
00:54:07.988 --> 00:54:09.697
That dude is weird.

639
00:54:13.201 --> 00:54:15.870
Jake.
your dad says you have mono.

640
00:54:16.455 --> 00:54:19.624
He won't let me visit.
but would you call me?

641
00:54:25.172 --> 00:54:27.798
Hey. it's me again. I just...

642
00:54:28.842 --> 00:54:31.761
I'm sorry about what I
said at the movie theater.

643
00:54:32.846 --> 00:54:36.057
I just wanted to hear your
voice. so no pressure.

644
00:54:39.186 --> 00:54:40.603
Jacob. please...

645
00:54:42.564 --> 00:54:43.939
Call me.

646
00:54:44.024 --> 00:54:46.651
Okay. We should be back around 3:00.

647
00:54:53.700 --> 00:54:54.867
Hey.

648
00:54:55.786 --> 00:54:57.787
Look. I don't have
to go fishing today.

649
00:54:57.871 --> 00:54:59.288
Yes. you do.

650
00:54:59.665 --> 00:55:02.291
Yeah. you do. Go. What
are you talking about?

651
00:55:02.376 --> 00:55:04.043
Just be careful.

652
00:55:04.127 --> 00:55:05.586
Always am.

653
00:55:07.255 --> 00:55:09.757
Those bears won't get
the drop on me. Bella.

654
00:55:09.841 --> 00:55:11.842
My kung fu is strong.

655
00:55:45.085 --> 00:55:46.252
Jake!

656
00:55:47.254 --> 00:55:48.504
Hey!

657
00:55:53.343 --> 00:55:55.302
You cut your hair off?

658
00:55:58.140 --> 00:55:59.974
And got a tattoo?

659
00:56:03.311 --> 00:56:04.520
Bella.

660
00:56:04.604 --> 00:56:07.565
I thought you were too
sick to come outside

661
00:56:08.483 --> 00:56:11.193
or pick up the
phone when I call.

662
00:56:12.446 --> 00:56:13.779
Go away.

663
00:56:15.115 --> 00:56:16.282
What?

664
00:56:17.951 --> 00:56:19.285
Go away.

665
00:56:21.246 --> 00:56:23.414
What happened to you? What's...

666
00:56:23.498 --> 00:56:25.791
Hey! What happened?

667
00:56:28.754 --> 00:56:31.797
Did Sam get to you? Is
that what's happening?

668
00:56:31.882 --> 00:56:35.176
Sam's trying to help me.
Don't blame him.

669
00:56:36.303 --> 00:56:38.763
But if you want
somebody to blame.

670
00:56:38.930 --> 00:56:42.850
how about those filthy bloodsuckers
you love. the Cullens?

671
00:56:50.066 --> 00:56:51.192
I don't know what
you're talking about.

672
00:56:51.276 --> 00:56:53.986
No. you know exactly
what I'm talking about.

673
00:56:54.070 --> 00:56:56.864
You've been lying to everyone.
Charlie.

674
00:56:59.159 --> 00:57:01.202
But you can't lie to me.

675
00:57:02.287 --> 00:57:04.455
Not anymore. Bella.
Jacob!

676
00:57:05.123 --> 00:57:06.457
Jacob!

677
00:57:12.506 --> 00:57:14.006
Look. Bella.

678
00:57:15.217 --> 00:57:17.551
we can't be friends anymore.

679
00:57:18.428 --> 00:57:22.223
Look. Jake.
I know that I've been hurting you.

680
00:57:23.892 --> 00:57:26.894
It's killing me. It kills me.

681
00:57:29.189 --> 00:57:31.982
I just need... Maybe
give me. like.

682
00:57:32.067 --> 00:57:34.068
some time or something.
Look. don't.

683
00:57:35.028 --> 00:57:36.570
It's not you.

684
00:57:39.449 --> 00:57:42.368
It's not you. it's me. right?
Really?

685
00:57:43.286 --> 00:57:45.621
It's true. It is me.

686
00:57:48.583 --> 00:57:50.709
I'm not good.

687
00:57:53.505 --> 00:57:56.715
I used to be a good kid.

688
00:57:58.051 --> 00:57:59.426
Not anymore.

689
00:58:00.595 --> 00:58:03.222
This doesn't even matter.
All right?

690
00:58:03.515 --> 00:58:04.515
This is over.

691
00:58:04.599 --> 00:58:06.767
You can't break up with me.

692
00:58:08.687 --> 00:58:09.937
I mean...

693
00:58:11.356 --> 00:58:13.607
I mean. you're my best friend.

694
00:58:16.111 --> 00:58:17.862
You promised me.

695
00:58:19.322 --> 00:58:20.656
I know.

696
00:58:21.491 --> 00:58:24.243
I promised I wouldn't
hurt you. Bella.

697
00:58:25.078 --> 00:58:27.621
And this is me keeping
that promise.

698
00:58:28.415 --> 00:58:29.748
Go home

699
00:58:30.458 --> 00:58:33.919
and don't come back or
you're gonna get hurt.

700
00:58:47.434 --> 00:58:48.767
Alice.

701
00:58:49.811 --> 00:58:51.312
things are...

702
00:58:52.939 --> 00:58:54.815
Things are bad again.

703
00:58:56.026 --> 00:58:59.153
Without Jake. I just...
I can't stand it.

704
00:59:02.490 --> 00:59:04.783
I don't see Edward anymore.

705
00:59:06.244 --> 00:59:09.163
Will it really feel
like he never existed?

706
00:59:16.671 --> 00:59:19.840
I will find the place where
I can see him again.

707
01:00:15.105 --> 01:00:16.313
Bella.

708
01:00:17.357 --> 01:00:18.607
Laurent.

709
01:00:20.610 --> 01:00:23.112
I didn't expect
to find you here.

710
01:00:25.240 --> 01:00:29.576
I went to visit the Cullens.
but the house is empty.

711
01:00:31.913 --> 01:00:34.415
I'm surprised they
left you behind.

712
01:00:34.624 --> 01:00:36.625
Weren't you sort of

713
01:00:37.752 --> 01:00:39.378
a pet of theirs?

714
01:00:40.338 --> 01:00:41.880
Yeah. You could say that.

715
01:00:41.965 --> 01:00:44.299
Do the Cullens visit often?

716
01:00:49.514 --> 01:00:50.514
Lie.

717
01:00:56.104 --> 01:00:57.396
Yeah. absolutely. all the time.

718
01:00:57.480 --> 01:00:59.023
Lie better.

719
01:00:59.107 --> 01:01:01.734
I'll tell them that
you stopped by.

720
01:01:02.318 --> 01:01:04.528
But I probably shouldn't

721
01:01:04.988 --> 01:01:07.656
tell Edward.

722
01:01:09.451 --> 01:01:10.826
'cause he's pretty protective.

723
01:01:10.910 --> 01:01:13.120
But he's far away. isn't he?

724
01:01:15.999 --> 01:01:17.750
Why are you here?

725
01:01:17.834 --> 01:01:22.212
I came as a favor to Victoria.

726
01:01:25.675 --> 01:01:27.217
Victoria?
She asked me to see

727
01:01:27.302 --> 01:01:30.888
if you were still under the
protection of the Cullens.

728
01:01:30.972 --> 01:01:34.391
Victoria feels it's only
fair to kill Edward's mate.

729
01:01:34.934 --> 01:01:36.602
given he killed hers.

730
01:01:36.686 --> 01:01:38.479
An eye for an eye.

731
01:01:39.147 --> 01:01:40.314
Threaten him.

732
01:01:40.398 --> 01:01:43.901
Edward would know who did it.
And he'd come after you.

733
01:01:44.944 --> 01:01:46.862
I don't think he will.

734
01:01:48.073 --> 01:01:51.033
After all. how much
could you mean to him

735
01:01:51.493 --> 01:01:53.994
if he left you here unprotected?

736
01:01:56.331 --> 01:01:59.333
Victoria won't be happy
about my killing you.

737
01:01:59.417 --> 01:02:01.418
but I can't help myself.

738
01:02:01.711 --> 01:02:03.462
You are so mouth-watering.

739
01:02:03.546 --> 01:02:07.257
Please. don't. I mean. you helped us.
No. no. no. no.

740
01:02:08.468 --> 01:02:11.720
Don't be afraid. I'm
doing you a kindness.

741
01:02:12.013 --> 01:02:14.681
Victoria plans on killing you
slowly.

742
01:02:15.975 --> 01:02:17.309
painfully.

743
01:02:18.269 --> 01:02:20.521
whereas I'll make it quick.

744
01:02:20.855 --> 01:02:22.231
I promise.

745
01:02:23.233 --> 01:02:25.234
You will feel nothing.

746
01:02:30.990 --> 01:02:32.616
Edward. I love you.

747
01:02:34.994 --> 01:02:36.662
I don't believe it.

748
01:03:43.730 --> 01:03:46.273
Dad! I saw them.
What's the matter?

749
01:03:46.357 --> 01:03:49.359
In the woods. They're not bears.
What do you mean in the woods?

750
01:03:49.444 --> 01:03:51.195
Bell. what the hell were you
doing out in the woods?

751
01:03:51.279 --> 01:03:54.990
They're wolves. I mean.
they're like huge wolves.

752
01:03:55.074 --> 01:03:56.909
Are you sure about that. Bella?

753
01:03:56.993 --> 01:04:00.204
Yeah! I just saw them.
They were after something.

754
01:04:01.414 --> 01:04:02.623
Wolves?

755
01:04:03.791 --> 01:04:05.292
You saw them?

756
01:04:07.921 --> 01:04:10.464
All right. well. Harry.

757
01:04:11.758 --> 01:04:15.093
feel like going hunting? Get
some of your guys together?

758
01:04:15.553 --> 01:04:17.596
Sure. yeah. I'll just...

759
01:04:19.349 --> 01:04:21.183
By now. those wolves will be dead.

760
01:04:22.810 --> 01:04:25.854
and Laurent would have
told her I'm unprotected.

761
01:04:25.939 --> 01:04:27.189
Victoria.

762
01:04:28.942 --> 01:04:30.400
I should go to the station.

763
01:04:30.485 --> 01:04:32.945
Yeah. you should. You should go.

764
01:04:33.571 --> 01:04:35.948
Can you just stay in the house?

765
01:05:00.974 --> 01:05:02.224
Bella!

766
01:05:04.894 --> 01:05:06.311
You scared me.

767
01:05:06.396 --> 01:05:09.856
What the hell are you doing?
Back up. I'm coming up.

768
01:05:22.120 --> 01:05:23.328
Hey.

769
01:05:25.498 --> 01:05:27.207
Look. I'm sorry.

770
01:05:34.257 --> 01:05:36.550
For what?
I wish I could explain.

771
01:05:36.634 --> 01:05:39.761
But I literally can't.

772
01:05:48.521 --> 01:05:51.898
Have you ever had a secret
you couldn't tell anyone.

773
01:05:52.817 --> 01:05:55.277
one that wasn't yours to share?

774
01:05:58.197 --> 01:06:00.741
Well. that's what
it's like for me.

775
01:06:00.992 --> 01:06:02.326
But worse.

776
01:06:03.703 --> 01:06:07.080
You have no idea how
tight I'm bound.

777
01:06:08.249 --> 01:06:09.708
I hate this.

778
01:06:10.626 --> 01:06:12.627
I hate what they've done to you.

779
01:06:27.101 --> 01:06:30.187
I mean. the killer part
is. you already know.

780
01:06:34.275 --> 01:06:38.987
Bella. do you remember when we
walked on the beach at La Push?

781
01:06:40.531 --> 01:06:41.823
The...

782
01:06:45.828 --> 01:06:48.497
The story. The story about

783
01:06:49.791 --> 01:06:51.458
the cold ones.

784
01:06:53.169 --> 01:06:56.922
I guess I understand why that's
the only part you remember.

785
01:07:03.930 --> 01:07:07.766
There's gotta be something
that you can do.

786
01:07:07.850 --> 01:07:09.893
No. I'm in it for life.

787
01:07:11.312 --> 01:07:13.939
Well. maybe we should just
get out of here for a while.

788
01:07:14.023 --> 01:07:15.899
Just leave.

789
01:07:15.983 --> 01:07:17.609
just you and me.

790
01:07:18.027 --> 01:07:19.653
You'd do that?

791
01:07:22.782 --> 01:07:24.741
I would do it for you.

792
01:07:30.998 --> 01:07:34.376
It's not something I can
just run away from. Bella.

793
01:07:35.336 --> 01:07:38.839
But I would run away with you

794
01:07:43.094 --> 01:07:44.511
if I could.

795
01:07:48.641 --> 01:07:51.852
I gotta go. They'll start
wondering where I am.

796
01:07:56.023 --> 01:07:57.524
Come here.

797
01:08:01.779 --> 01:08:03.071
Please.

798
01:08:04.115 --> 01:08:05.907
try to remember.

799
01:08:07.535 --> 01:08:09.661
It'd be so much easier

800
01:08:10.872 --> 01:08:12.497
if you knew.

801
01:08:14.959 --> 01:08:17.502
I'll try. But. Jake...

802
01:08:18.296 --> 01:08:21.047
Jake. what are you doing?
Wait. Jake.

803
01:08:28.181 --> 01:08:29.347
Jake.

804
01:08:46.240 --> 01:08:47.991
Edward. I'm scared.

805
01:08:48.576 --> 01:08:50.202
You should be.

806
01:08:55.249 --> 01:08:57.167
Really. it's just like an old story.

807
01:08:57.251 --> 01:08:59.171
I'm not really supposed
to say anything about it.

808
01:08:59.212 --> 01:09:03.006
Did you know Quileutes are
supposedly descended from wolves?

809
01:09:17.855 --> 01:09:19.105
Bella?

810
01:09:19.524 --> 01:09:21.274
I need to see him.

811
01:09:21.984 --> 01:09:23.527
He's not in.

812
01:09:25.196 --> 01:09:28.490
Okay. I'm sorry. I really need to see him.
Bella!

813
01:09:44.465 --> 01:09:46.132
What did you do?

814
01:09:47.134 --> 01:09:48.255
Okay. what did you do?
Hey.

815
01:09:48.261 --> 01:09:49.636
What did you do to him?
Easy!

816
01:09:49.720 --> 01:09:50.762
He didn't want this.

817
01:09:50.846 --> 01:09:53.223
What did we do? What did he do?
What'd he tell you?

818
01:09:53.307 --> 01:09:54.724
Both of you calm down.
Nothing.

819
01:09:54.809 --> 01:09:57.894
He tells me nothing because
he's scared of you.

820
01:10:03.025 --> 01:10:04.943
Too late now.
Bella. get back!

821
01:10:06.153 --> 01:10:08.863
Paul. calm down. now!

822
01:10:17.498 --> 01:10:18.748
Bella!

823
01:10:20.001 --> 01:10:21.126
Run!

824
01:10:24.338 --> 01:10:25.672
Jake. run!

825
01:10:51.866 --> 01:10:53.033
Paul!

826
01:11:03.711 --> 01:11:06.379
Hey! Take Bella back
to Emily's place.

827
01:11:08.049 --> 01:11:10.467
Guess the wolf's out of the bag.

828
01:11:15.473 --> 01:11:19.351
Alice. is it possible
that everything is true?

829
01:11:20.061 --> 01:11:22.437
The fairy tales and
horror stories?

830
01:11:22.521 --> 01:11:26.066
Is it possible that there isn't
anything sane or normal at all?

831
01:11:28.235 --> 01:11:30.153
Hey. I think we should go
back and see if Jacob's okay.

832
01:11:30.237 --> 01:11:32.864
I hope Paul sinks some teeth
in him. Serves him right.

833
01:11:32.948 --> 01:11:34.741
No way. Jacob's a natural.

834
01:11:34.825 --> 01:11:38.536
You see him phase on the fly? I got
five says Paul doesn't touch him.

835
01:11:38.621 --> 01:11:41.081
Come on in. Bella.
We won't bite.

836
01:11:41.415 --> 01:11:43.166
Speak for yourself.

837
01:11:44.377 --> 01:11:46.336
I done me wrong.

838
01:11:46.420 --> 01:11:48.630
And done all wrong.

839
01:11:49.840 --> 01:11:52.842
All the wrong I've done I'm
sure I'll live quite long.

840
01:11:52.927 --> 01:11:57.514
Oh. hey. about Emily. Sam's
fiancÃ©e? Don't stare. It bugs Sam.

841
01:12:00.142 --> 01:12:01.851
Why would I stare?

842
01:12:01.936 --> 01:12:05.021
Are you guys hungry?
Like I have to ask.

843
01:12:12.446 --> 01:12:14.030
Who's this?

844
01:12:14.115 --> 01:12:15.949
Bella Swan. Who else?

845
01:12:17.618 --> 01:12:18.660
Hmm.

846
01:12:18.744 --> 01:12:20.995
So. you're the vampire girl.

847
01:12:24.041 --> 01:12:26.126
So. you're the wolf girl.

848
01:12:28.963 --> 01:12:30.380
Guess so.

849
01:12:30.464 --> 01:12:33.049
Well. I'm engaged to one.

850
01:12:36.387 --> 01:12:40.932
Save some for your brothers.
And ladies first. Muffin?

851
01:12:41.976 --> 01:12:43.435
Sure. Thanks.

852
01:12:43.519 --> 01:12:47.021
Leave it to Jacob to find a
way around Sam's gag order.

853
01:12:47.815 --> 01:12:49.733
He didn't say anything to me.

854
01:12:49.817 --> 01:12:50.984
That's a wolf thing.

855
01:12:51.068 --> 01:12:53.570
Alpha's orders get obeyed
whether we want them to or not.

856
01:12:53.654 --> 01:12:55.905
And check it out. We can
hear each other's thoughts.

857
01:12:55.990 --> 01:12:59.826
Would you shut up? These are
trade secrets. Damn it!

858
01:13:00.161 --> 01:13:02.495
This chick runs with vampires.

859
01:13:03.497 --> 01:13:06.082
You can't really
run with vampires.

860
01:13:08.043 --> 01:13:09.919
'Cause they're fast.

861
01:13:10.171 --> 01:13:12.922
Yeah? Well. we're faster.

862
01:13:14.341 --> 01:13:16.009
Freaked out yet?

863
01:13:17.720 --> 01:13:20.096
You're not the first
monsters I've met.

864
01:13:20.181 --> 01:13:23.016
Jake's right. You're good with weird.

865
01:13:24.810 --> 01:13:25.977
Hey.

866
01:13:45.372 --> 01:13:46.706
Sorry.

867
01:14:01.180 --> 01:14:03.056
So you're a werewolf?

868
01:14:04.850 --> 01:14:07.227
Yeah. Last time I checked.

869
01:14:09.480 --> 01:14:12.565
A few lucky members of
the tribe have the gene.

870
01:14:12.900 --> 01:14:16.736
A bloodsucker moves into
town and the fever sets in.

871
01:14:19.323 --> 01:14:20.406
Mono.

872
01:14:22.159 --> 01:14:23.701
Yeah. I wish.

873
01:14:26.956 --> 01:14:31.042
Well. can't you find
a way to just stop?

874
01:14:33.587 --> 01:14:35.588
I mean. it's wrong.

875
01:14:38.175 --> 01:14:40.718
It's not a lifestyle
choice. Bella.

876
01:14:41.136 --> 01:14:43.847
I was born this way.
I can't help it.

877
01:14:43.931 --> 01:14:47.100
You're such a hypocrite. What. I'm not
the right kind of monster for you?

878
01:14:47.184 --> 01:14:49.102
It's not what you are.

879
01:14:49.520 --> 01:14:52.897
It's what you do. They
never hurt anybody.

880
01:14:55.317 --> 01:14:56.734
You've killed people. Jake.

881
01:14:56.819 --> 01:14:59.237
Bella. we're not killing anyone.

882
01:15:01.282 --> 01:15:02.699
Then who is?

883
01:15:02.783 --> 01:15:05.743
What we're trying to
protect you people from.

884
01:15:05.995 --> 01:15:08.121
the only thing we do kill.

885
01:15:10.499 --> 01:15:11.791
vampires.

886
01:15:13.294 --> 01:15:14.377
Wait. Jake. you can't.

887
01:15:14.461 --> 01:15:16.713
Don't worry. We can't touch
your little precious Cullens

888
01:15:16.797 --> 01:15:19.257
unless they violate the treaty.

889
01:15:19.800 --> 01:15:21.968
That's not what I'm saying.

890
01:15:22.261 --> 01:15:24.804
You can't kill vampires.
They'll...

891
01:15:25.306 --> 01:15:26.973
They'll kill you.

892
01:15:27.141 --> 01:15:30.560
Really? We took out that leech
with the dreads easy enough.

893
01:15:34.982 --> 01:15:36.107
Laurent?

894
01:15:36.191 --> 01:15:38.860
And his red-headed girlfriend is next.

895
01:15:39.320 --> 01:15:40.695
Victoria's here?

896
01:15:40.779 --> 01:15:43.781
Was. We chased her all the way to the
Canadian border the other night.

897
01:15:43.866 --> 01:15:47.285
She keeps coming back. We
don't know what she's after.

898
01:15:47.369 --> 01:15:48.703
I do.

899
01:15:52.082 --> 01:15:53.207
Me.

900
01:16:02.343 --> 01:16:05.178
Don't worry. We've got
this place covered.

901
01:16:05.846 --> 01:16:08.306
She won't get near
you or Charlie.

902
01:16:08.849 --> 01:16:10.600
Look. you've got to be careful.

903
01:16:10.684 --> 01:16:13.770
She's fast. You don't
know how fast she is.

904
01:16:13.854 --> 01:16:17.732
You know. your lack of confidence
in us is a little insulting.

905
01:16:19.234 --> 01:16:21.110
All right. I'd better go.

906
01:16:22.488 --> 01:16:24.030
You gotta go?

907
01:16:24.949 --> 01:16:26.115
Yeah.

908
01:16:26.867 --> 01:16:28.993
Got a vampire to kill.

909
01:16:42.633 --> 01:16:45.176
Alice. I'm all right.

910
01:16:46.845 --> 01:16:48.596
Until I'm alone.

911
01:16:49.890 --> 01:16:52.350
And lately. that's all the time.

912
01:16:52.768 --> 01:16:55.478
Jacob's gone. He's
hunting Victoria.

913
01:16:55.562 --> 01:16:57.814
And Charlie's hunting Jacob.

914
01:16:57.898 --> 01:16:59.565
And you're gone.

915
01:17:00.567 --> 01:17:02.318
And so is Edward.

916
01:17:06.323 --> 01:17:08.700
And there's just nothing now.

917
01:17:11.745 --> 01:17:13.746
You got something. Harry?

918
01:17:14.957 --> 01:17:16.582
Nope. Nothing.

919
01:17:24.258 --> 01:17:26.175
But I realize where
I have to go.

920
01:17:26.260 --> 01:17:28.803
what I have to do
to see him again.

921
01:17:40.607 --> 01:17:43.151
A tear in my brain.

922
01:17:48.615 --> 01:17:52.243
Allows the voices in.

923
01:17:58.625 --> 01:18:01.961
They wanna push
you off the path.

924
01:18:06.675 --> 01:18:10.178
With their frequency wires.

925
01:18:17.603 --> 01:18:21.314
And you can do no wrong.

926
01:18:27.613 --> 01:18:34.160
In my eyes.

927
01:18:36.371 --> 01:18:39.874
You can do no wrong.

928
01:18:46.131 --> 01:18:52.845
In my eyes.

929
01:18:54.807 --> 01:18:56.849
A drunken salesman.

930
01:18:56.934 --> 01:18:58.851
Your hearing damage.

931
01:18:58.936 --> 01:19:00.812
Your mind is restless.

932
01:19:00.896 --> 01:19:02.980
They say you're getting better.

933
01:19:03.065 --> 01:19:06.317
But you don't feel any better.

934
01:19:13.408 --> 01:19:15.451
Your speakers are blowing.

935
01:19:15.536 --> 01:19:17.620
Your ears are wrecking.

936
01:19:17.704 --> 01:19:19.622
Your hearing damage.

937
01:19:19.706 --> 01:19:24.210
You wish you felt better.

938
01:19:32.302 --> 01:19:36.055
You can do no wrong.

939
01:19:42.229 --> 01:19:52.238
In my eyes

940
01:20:26.773 --> 01:20:28.316
Don't do this.

941
01:20:33.280 --> 01:20:35.406
You wanted me to be human.

942
01:20:37.910 --> 01:20:39.243
Watch me.

943
01:20:41.997 --> 01:20:43.289
Please.

944
01:20:44.583 --> 01:20:45.583
For me.

945
01:20:45.667 --> 01:20:48.336
You won't stay with
me any other way.

946
01:20:51.048 --> 01:20:52.965
Bella. please.

947
01:21:55.445 --> 01:22:01.867
This constant noise
all the time.

948
01:22:12.337 --> 01:22:18.217
Even though you're
the only one I see.

949
01:22:21.179 --> 01:22:22.430
Breathe!

950
01:22:24.182 --> 01:22:25.224
Breathe!

951
01:22:26.893 --> 01:22:28.936
Come on. Bella. breathe!

952
01:22:36.028 --> 01:22:38.654
Bella? Bella. can you hear me?

953
01:22:44.995 --> 01:22:46.370
Jake?

954
01:22:47.789 --> 01:22:49.206
Come here.

955
01:22:54.588 --> 01:22:56.964
What the hell were you thinking?

956
01:22:58.091 --> 01:23:00.301
I just wanted to see something.

957
01:23:00.761 --> 01:23:04.472
Get her home! I'm gonna go help
out over at Harry's place.

958
01:23:07.476 --> 01:23:09.518
What happened at Harry's?

959
01:23:09.770 --> 01:23:12.438
Harry Clearwater had
a heart attack.

960
01:23:13.106 --> 01:23:15.691
Charlie and my dad are over
at his place with his family.

961
01:23:15.776 --> 01:23:17.276
Is he okay?

962
01:23:19.446 --> 01:23:20.780
He's gone.

963
01:23:24.493 --> 01:23:28.037
Come on. I'll get you something
dry and drive you home.

964
01:23:39.216 --> 01:23:41.801
108Â° over here.

965
01:23:43.678 --> 01:23:44.887
God!

966
01:23:46.014 --> 01:23:47.973
My hands are freezing.

967
01:23:50.102 --> 01:23:52.645
It must be nice.
never getting cold.

968
01:23:52.979 --> 01:23:54.688
It's a wolf thing.

969
01:23:55.482 --> 01:23:56.816
It's not.

970
01:23:57.484 --> 01:23:59.318
It's a Jacob thing.

971
01:23:59.820 --> 01:24:01.654
You're just warm.

972
01:24:04.032 --> 01:24:05.991
You're like your own sun.

973
01:24:09.579 --> 01:24:13.290
This is better. now
that you know about me.

974
01:24:16.628 --> 01:24:17.837
But...

975
01:24:23.135 --> 01:24:25.511
You saw what happened to Emily.

976
01:24:28.849 --> 01:24:30.433
Sam got angry.

977
01:24:31.351 --> 01:24:33.561
Lost it for a split second.

978
01:24:34.980 --> 01:24:37.064
Em was standing too close.

979
01:24:39.484 --> 01:24:42.194
He'll never be able
to take that back.

980
01:24:44.823 --> 01:24:46.866
What if I got mad at you?

981
01:24:58.295 --> 01:24:59.753
Sometimes.

982
01:25:02.340 --> 01:25:04.884
I feel like I'm gonna disappear.

983
01:25:11.475 --> 01:25:13.726
Okay. not that you need me

984
01:25:14.394 --> 01:25:16.729
to tell you something like this.

985
01:25:18.356 --> 01:25:21.942
but I always will. You're
not gonna lose yourself.

986
01:25:24.863 --> 01:25:27.031
I wouldn't let that happen.

987
01:25:29.284 --> 01:25:30.534
How?

988
01:25:33.997 --> 01:25:36.290
I'll tell you all the time

989
01:25:39.920 --> 01:25:41.921
how special you are.

990
01:26:01.399 --> 01:26:03.609
Thank you. For everything.

991
01:26:10.659 --> 01:26:11.825
Wait.

992
01:26:14.621 --> 01:26:16.330
There's a vampire.

993
01:26:16.790 --> 01:26:18.499
How do you know?

994
01:26:18.750 --> 01:26:21.794
I can smell it. I'm
getting you out of here.

995
01:26:22.629 --> 01:26:24.171
That's Carlisle's car.

996
01:26:25.715 --> 01:26:27.216
They're here.

997
01:26:27.592 --> 01:26:31.136
Bella. it's a trick! Stop!
You gotta come with me!

998
01:26:34.683 --> 01:26:36.308
They won't hurt me.

999
01:26:36.393 --> 01:26:39.812
If a Cullen is back here.
this is their territory.

1000
01:26:40.230 --> 01:26:42.648
Treaty says we can only
defend on our own lands.

1001
01:26:42.732 --> 01:26:46.819
I can't protect you here.
Okay. That's okay. You don't have to.

1002
01:26:49.322 --> 01:26:51.073
You're about to cross a line.

1003
01:26:51.157 --> 01:26:53.075
Then don't draw one.

1004
01:26:53.368 --> 01:26:54.660
Please?

1005
01:27:11.553 --> 01:27:12.761
Alice?

1006
01:27:13.054 --> 01:27:15.639
Oh. my God! What are you...
Bella!

1007
01:27:16.266 --> 01:27:20.436
I'm sorry. I just. I can't
believe you're here. Is...

1008
01:27:20.520 --> 01:27:23.856
Would you like to explain
to me how you're alive?

1009
01:27:24.566 --> 01:27:25.608
What?

1010
01:27:25.692 --> 01:27:28.861
I saw a vision of you.
You jumped off a cliff.

1011
01:27:29.821 --> 01:27:31.947
Why in the hell would you
try and kill yourself?

1012
01:27:32.032 --> 01:27:33.157
I mean. what about Charlie?

1013
01:27:33.241 --> 01:27:35.993
What about...
I didn't try to kill myself.

1014
01:27:36.077 --> 01:27:37.536
I was cliff jumping.

1015
01:27:37.621 --> 01:27:39.371
Recreationally.

1016
01:27:39.456 --> 01:27:40.873
It was fun.

1017
01:27:43.084 --> 01:27:47.087
I have never met anyone
more prone to life-threatening idiocy.

1018
01:27:52.594 --> 01:27:53.719
Does...

1019
01:27:54.262 --> 01:27:56.305
Did you tell him?

1020
01:27:56.389 --> 01:27:57.473
No.

1021
01:27:59.142 --> 01:28:01.894
He only calls in once
every few months.

1022
01:28:03.480 --> 01:28:05.731
He said he wants to be alone.

1023
01:28:11.571 --> 01:28:14.948
Bella. what is that
God-awful wet dog smell?

1024
01:28:16.409 --> 01:28:17.409
Um...

1025
01:28:18.244 --> 01:28:19.995
That's probably me.

1026
01:28:20.997 --> 01:28:23.248
Or it's Jacob.

1027
01:28:24.501 --> 01:28:25.918
Jacob who?

1028
01:28:27.253 --> 01:28:29.380
Jacob's kind of a werewolf.

1029
01:28:30.965 --> 01:28:34.093
Bella! Werewolves are not
good company to keep.

1030
01:28:35.387 --> 01:28:37.262
Speak for yourself.

1031
01:28:42.102 --> 01:28:44.269
I had to see you were safe.

1032
01:28:45.814 --> 01:28:48.607
I thought you couldn't
protect me here.

1033
01:28:48.858 --> 01:28:50.609
Guess I don't care.

1034
01:28:54.322 --> 01:28:56.615
Well. I'm not gonna hurt her.

1035
01:28:58.201 --> 01:29:00.119
No. you're just a
harmless Cullen.

1036
01:29:00.203 --> 01:29:03.622
I'm talking about the other bloodsucker
who tried to kill Bella because of you.

1037
01:29:03.707 --> 01:29:04.748
Victoria?

1038
01:29:04.833 --> 01:29:06.959
Yeah. Victoria's been around.

1039
01:29:07.043 --> 01:29:08.794
I didn't see her.

1040
01:29:09.295 --> 01:29:12.840
I didn't see you get pulled
out of the water. either.

1041
01:29:13.758 --> 01:29:16.719
I can't see past you and
your pack of mutts.

1042
01:29:16.803 --> 01:29:18.929
Don't get me upset...

1043
01:29:19.013 --> 01:29:23.183
Hey. stop. Stop. stop. stop. stop.
Or things are gonna get very ugly.

1044
01:29:28.565 --> 01:29:30.482
I'll give you a minute.

1045
01:29:36.489 --> 01:29:37.573
Hey.

1046
01:29:38.658 --> 01:29:41.243
You're not going anywhere.
You're gonna come back.

1047
01:29:41.327 --> 01:29:44.121
right?
As soon as you put the dog out.

1048
01:29:53.131 --> 01:29:54.506
Is he...

1049
01:29:58.636 --> 01:30:00.179
Are there others? How
many Cullens are here

1050
01:30:00.263 --> 01:30:02.431
and how long are they staying?

1051
01:30:02.515 --> 01:30:03.640
No.

1052
01:30:04.517 --> 01:30:06.268
It's just Alice.

1053
01:30:10.899 --> 01:30:13.692
And she can stay as
long as she'd like.

1054
01:30:16.154 --> 01:30:18.489
Well. are the rest coming back?

1055
01:30:24.788 --> 01:30:25.871
No.

1056
01:30:27.707 --> 01:30:29.124
Not that I know of.

1057
01:30:30.335 --> 01:30:31.877
Anything else?

1058
01:30:36.174 --> 01:30:37.549
That's it.

1059
01:30:39.719 --> 01:30:43.388
Well. if that's all. then you'd
better go run back to Sam.

1060
01:30:46.476 --> 01:30:48.268
I've done it again.

1061
01:30:49.229 --> 01:30:51.396
I keep breaking my promise.

1062
01:30:56.653 --> 01:30:59.404
We don't have to do
this to each other.

1063
01:31:03.868 --> 01:31:05.410
Yes. we do.

1064
01:31:17.257 --> 01:31:18.590
Bella...

1065
01:31:41.489 --> 01:31:43.115
Swan residence.

1066
01:31:48.872 --> 01:31:50.956
He's not here right now.

1067
01:31:51.666 --> 01:31:53.584
He's arranging a funeral.

1068
01:32:09.517 --> 01:32:11.143
Who was that?

1069
01:32:11.436 --> 01:32:12.477
What?

1070
01:32:12.562 --> 01:32:14.354
Always in the way.

1071
01:32:16.524 --> 01:32:17.733
Who was that?

1072
01:32:17.817 --> 01:32:19.443
Bella. step back.

1073
01:32:19.527 --> 01:32:22.738
Jake. who was that?
Bella! Bella. it's Edward.

1074
01:32:23.323 --> 01:32:26.742
He thinks you're dead. Rosalie
told him why I came here.

1075
01:32:28.953 --> 01:32:31.663
Why would you... Why didn't
you let me speak to him?

1076
01:32:31.748 --> 01:32:32.948
He didn't ask for you.
Bella.

1077
01:32:32.999 --> 01:32:36.585
I don't care!
Bella. Bella! He's going to the Volturi.

1078
01:32:37.253 --> 01:32:39.171
He wants to die. too.

1079
01:32:41.090 --> 01:32:44.217
He left you. Bella.
He didn't want you anymore. Remember?

1080
01:32:44.302 --> 01:32:47.763
No. I'm not gonna let him
kill himself out of guilt.

1081
01:32:48.473 --> 01:32:50.307
What about your dad?

1082
01:32:50.850 --> 01:32:54.227
I'm 18. I'm legally free
to go. and I left a note.

1083
01:32:56.022 --> 01:32:57.731
Please. Bella.

1084
01:32:59.192 --> 01:33:01.276
just stay here.

1085
01:33:03.029 --> 01:33:04.529
For Charlie.

1086
01:33:07.367 --> 01:33:08.909
Or for me.

1087
01:33:09.953 --> 01:33:11.495
I have to go.

1088
01:33:17.460 --> 01:33:19.211
I'm begging you.

1089
01:33:21.881 --> 01:33:23.256
Please.

1090
01:33:25.009 --> 01:33:26.635
Goodbye. Jacob.

1091
01:33:35.144 --> 01:33:36.353
Okay.

1092
01:34:37.790 --> 01:34:40.125
So you've made up your minds.

1093
01:34:40.376 --> 01:34:42.836
I'm afraid your particular gifts

1094
01:34:43.963 --> 01:34:46.298
are too valuable to destroy.

1095
01:34:47.258 --> 01:34:52.137
But if you're unhappy
with your lot. join us.

1096
01:34:53.264 --> 01:34:56.975
We would be delighted
to utilize your skills.

1097
01:34:57.935 --> 01:35:00.479
Won't you consider
staying with us?

1098
01:35:02.273 --> 01:35:04.608
You know it will happen anyway.

1099
01:35:04.692 --> 01:35:06.610
Not without 'cause.

1100
01:35:10.865 --> 01:35:12.449
Such a waste.

1101
01:35:19.665 --> 01:35:21.458
I'm guessing you
didn't rent this car?

1102
01:35:21.542 --> 01:35:23.662
I figured you wouldn't be
opposed to grand theft auto.

1103
01:35:23.669 --> 01:35:25.045
Not today.

1104
01:35:28.382 --> 01:35:30.050
What? What do you see?

1105
01:35:30.134 --> 01:35:32.010
They refused him.

1106
01:35:32.095 --> 01:35:34.513
So?
He's gonna make a scene.

1107
01:35:34.847 --> 01:35:37.682
Show himself to the humans.
No! When?

1108
01:35:38.726 --> 01:35:41.770
He's gonna wait until noon.
when the sun's at it's highest.

1109
01:35:44.524 --> 01:35:45.804
God. Alice. you got to hurry up.

1110
01:35:45.817 --> 01:35:47.692
There's Volterra.

1111
01:36:12.468 --> 01:36:15.303
Why are they all in red?
San Marco's Day festival.

1112
01:36:15.388 --> 01:36:18.181
They're commemorating the expulsion
of vampires from the city.

1113
01:36:18.266 --> 01:36:19.599
It's the perfect setting.

1114
01:36:19.684 --> 01:36:22.227
The Volturi will never let him get
far enough to reveal himself.

1115
01:36:22.311 --> 01:36:24.020
We have five minutes.

1116
01:36:24.105 --> 01:36:26.398
I know. Bella. just breathe.

1117
01:36:32.488 --> 01:36:33.488
Alice!

1118
01:36:33.573 --> 01:36:35.740
Bella. you're the only
one he can't see coming.

1119
01:36:35.825 --> 01:36:38.910
If I go. he'll read my thoughts. He'll
think I'm lying. He'll rush into it.

1120
01:36:39.662 --> 01:36:42.998
Where do I go?
He'll be under the clock tower. Go!

1121
01:38:35.444 --> 01:38:36.778
Don't!

1122
01:38:38.864 --> 01:38:39.990
Heaven.

1123
01:38:40.074 --> 01:38:41.741
You have to move.

1124
01:38:42.576 --> 01:38:45.370
Open your eyes. Look at me.
I'm alive.

1125
01:38:46.122 --> 01:38:47.872
You have to move.

1126
01:38:48.708 --> 01:38:49.958
Bella.

1127
01:38:57.425 --> 01:38:59.551
You're here.
I'm here.

1128
01:39:02.388 --> 01:39:03.596
You're alive.

1129
01:39:07.059 --> 01:39:08.268
Yes.

1130
01:39:17.737 --> 01:39:20.322
I needed to make
you see me once.

1131
01:39:21.365 --> 01:39:22.686
You had to know
that I was alive.

1132
01:39:22.742 --> 01:39:25.869
that you didn't have to
feel guilty about anything.

1133
01:39:28.748 --> 01:39:31.333
I can let you go now.

1134
01:39:36.088 --> 01:39:38.256
I never acted out of guilt.

1135
01:39:40.718 --> 01:39:44.220
I just couldn't live in a
world where you don't exist.

1136
01:39:45.598 --> 01:39:47.640
But you said...
I lied.

1137
01:39:48.351 --> 01:39:51.436
I had to lie. But you
believed me so easily.

1138
01:39:57.109 --> 01:40:00.695
Because it doesn't make
sense for you to love me.

1139
01:40:03.407 --> 01:40:06.993
I mean. I'm nothing. I'm human.
I'm nothing.

1140
01:40:08.204 --> 01:40:11.790
Bella. you're everything to me.

1141
01:40:13.751 --> 01:40:15.460
You're everything.

1142
01:40:41.153 --> 01:40:43.273
I won't be needing your
services after all. gentlemen.

1143
01:40:43.322 --> 01:40:45.407
Aro wants to speak
with you again.

1144
01:40:45.491 --> 01:40:46.741
No rules were broken.

1145
01:40:46.826 --> 01:40:50.995
Nonetheless. we should take this
conversation to a more appropriate venue.

1146
01:40:51.080 --> 01:40:52.330
Fine.

1147
01:40:53.666 --> 01:40:56.000
Bella. why don't you go and
enjoy the rest of the festival?

1148
01:40:56.085 --> 01:40:57.419
The girl comes with us.

1149
01:40:57.503 --> 01:40:59.212
No. You can go to hell.

1150
01:41:01.590 --> 01:41:03.174
Come on. guys.

1151
01:41:03.426 --> 01:41:06.845
It's a festival. You wouldn't
want to make a scene.

1152
01:41:07.680 --> 01:41:09.097
We wouldn't.

1153
01:41:09.473 --> 01:41:10.807
Enough.

1154
01:41:12.351 --> 01:41:13.518
Jane.

1155
01:41:14.311 --> 01:41:17.313
Aro sent me to see what
was taking so long.

1156
01:41:25.364 --> 01:41:27.323
Just do as she says.

1157
01:41:39.879 --> 01:41:41.254
Go ahead.

1158
01:41:45.259 --> 01:41:46.926
Don't be scared.

1159
01:41:47.887 --> 01:41:49.220
Are you?

1160
01:41:50.181 --> 01:41:51.264
No.

1161
01:42:29.845 --> 01:42:31.971
Is she human?
Yes.

1162
01:42:35.142 --> 01:42:36.768
Does she know?

1163
01:42:37.269 --> 01:42:38.436
Yes.

1164
01:42:38.771 --> 01:42:40.563
Then. why would...

1165
01:42:42.191 --> 01:42:43.983
She wants to be.

1166
01:42:44.443 --> 01:42:45.860
And so she will be.

1167
01:42:45.945 --> 01:42:47.362
Or dessert.

1168
01:42:55.871 --> 01:42:59.666
Sister. They send you out to get one
and you bring back two.

1169
01:43:00.417 --> 01:43:01.876
And a half.

1170
01:43:03.045 --> 01:43:04.420
Such a clever girl.

1171
01:43:04.505 --> 01:43:06.422
What a happy surprise!

1172
01:43:07.466 --> 01:43:10.134
Bella is alive after all.

1173
01:43:11.011 --> 01:43:13.680
Isn't that wonderful?

1174
01:43:14.807 --> 01:43:16.683
I love a happy ending.

1175
01:43:17.810 --> 01:43:18.810
Ah.

1176
01:43:21.146 --> 01:43:22.981
They are so rare.

1177
01:43:29.822 --> 01:43:32.323
Her blood appeals to you so much

1178
01:43:33.617 --> 01:43:35.451
it makes me thirsty.

1179
01:43:35.703 --> 01:43:38.496
How can you stand to
be so close to her?

1180
01:43:38.664 --> 01:43:41.666
It's not without difficulty.
Yes. I can see that.

1181
01:43:45.087 --> 01:43:48.673
Aro can read every thought
I've ever had with one touch.

1182
01:43:49.675 --> 01:43:51.884
And now you know everything.

1183
01:43:52.511 --> 01:43:54.304
So get on with it.

1184
01:43:57.433 --> 01:44:00.643
You are quite a soul
reader yourself. Edward.

1185
01:44:02.271 --> 01:44:06.524
Though you can't read
Bella's thoughts.

1186
01:44:09.945 --> 01:44:11.404
Fascinating.

1187
01:44:14.950 --> 01:44:20.330
I would love to see if you are an
exception to my gifts. as well.

1188
01:44:23.042 --> 01:44:25.209
Would you do me the honor?

1189
01:44:46.065 --> 01:44:47.482
Interesting.

1190
01:44:47.858 --> 01:44:48.858
Hmm.

1191
01:44:49.652 --> 01:44:51.235
I see nothing.

1192
01:45:00.579 --> 01:45:02.121
I wonder if...

1193
01:45:02.956 --> 01:45:05.917
Let us see if she's
immune to all our powers.

1194
01:45:07.503 --> 01:45:08.961
Shall we. Jane?

1195
01:45:10.839 --> 01:45:12.590
No!
Pain.

1196
01:45:28.607 --> 01:45:29.941
Stop!

1197
01:45:30.776 --> 01:45:32.527
Stop! Please! Stop!

1198
01:45:32.611 --> 01:45:36.447
Stop! Just stop hurting him!
Please! Please!

1199
01:45:38.158 --> 01:45:39.409
Jane?

1200
01:45:41.495 --> 01:45:42.495
Master?

1201
01:45:47.084 --> 01:45:48.793
Go ahead. my dear.

1202
01:45:54.299 --> 01:45:56.509
This may hurt just a little.

1203
01:46:12.651 --> 01:46:14.152
Remarkable!

1204
01:46:16.363 --> 01:46:18.614
She confounds us all.

1205
01:46:19.658 --> 01:46:22.827
So what do we do with you now?

1206
01:46:23.370 --> 01:46:26.497
You already know what
you're going to do. Aro.

1207
01:46:27.499 --> 01:46:29.333
She knows too much.

1208
01:46:29.877 --> 01:46:31.669
She's a liability.

1209
01:46:33.005 --> 01:46:34.005
Hmm.

1210
01:46:35.632 --> 01:46:37.175
That's true.

1211
01:46:41.054 --> 01:46:42.346
Felix?

1212
01:46:46.226 --> 01:46:47.310
No!

1213
01:47:48.872 --> 01:47:51.958
Please! No! No! Please. please!

1214
01:47:54.837 --> 01:47:57.964
Kill me! Kill me! Not him.

1215
01:48:08.976 --> 01:48:11.519
How extraordinary.

1216
01:48:13.230 --> 01:48:17.650
You would give up your
life for someone like us.

1217
01:48:18.777 --> 01:48:20.111
A vampire.

1218
01:48:21.530 --> 01:48:23.948
A soulless monster.

1219
01:48:24.032 --> 01:48:26.033
Just get away from her!

1220
01:48:30.122 --> 01:48:34.584
You don't know a thing
about his soul.

1221
01:48:46.179 --> 01:48:47.889
This is a sadness.

1222
01:48:50.017 --> 01:48:53.603
If only it were your intention
to give her immortality.

1223
01:49:02.487 --> 01:49:03.779
Wait!

1224
01:49:05.407 --> 01:49:07.491
Bella will be one of us.

1225
01:49:09.202 --> 01:49:10.703
I've seen it.

1226
01:49:12.497 --> 01:49:14.415
I'll change her myself.

1227
01:49:48.325 --> 01:49:49.825
Mesmerizing.

1228
01:49:50.243 --> 01:49:54.664
To see what you have seen
before it has happened.

1229
01:49:57.584 --> 01:50:02.046
Your gifts will make
for an intriguing

1230
01:50:03.298 --> 01:50:04.715
immortal.

1231
01:50:05.801 --> 01:50:07.343
Isabella.

1232
01:50:12.224 --> 01:50:13.641
Go now.

1233
01:50:14.351 --> 01:50:16.310
Make your preparations.

1234
01:50:17.104 --> 01:50:19.105
Let us be done with this.

1235
01:50:20.941 --> 01:50:23.234
Heidi will arrive any moment.

1236
01:50:25.070 --> 01:50:28.489
Thank you for your visit.

1237
01:50:28.573 --> 01:50:30.116
We will return the favor.

1238
01:50:30.200 --> 01:50:33.160
I would advise that you follow
through on your promise soon.

1239
01:50:33.245 --> 01:50:35.579
We do not offer second chances.

1240
01:50:37.249 --> 01:50:40.334
Goodbye. my young friends.

1241
01:50:46.717 --> 01:50:48.509
Nice fishing. Heidi.

1242
01:50:48.593 --> 01:50:50.845
Yes. they do look rather juicy.

1243
01:50:50.929 --> 01:50:52.638
Save some for me.

1244
01:50:53.598 --> 01:50:56.434
This way. please. Stay together.

1245
01:51:11.074 --> 01:51:12.616
Stop! Stop!

1246
01:51:23.462 --> 01:51:25.004
You're here.

1247
01:51:27.049 --> 01:51:28.632
You can sleep.

1248
01:51:32.429 --> 01:51:35.056
I'll still be here when you wake-up.

1249
01:51:38.643 --> 01:51:41.687
Bella. the only reason I left

1250
01:51:43.482 --> 01:51:46.400
was because I thought
I was protecting you.

1251
01:51:48.278 --> 01:51:49.904
I needed you

1252
01:51:49.988 --> 01:51:53.949
to have a chance at a
normal. happy life.

1253
01:51:58.038 --> 01:52:00.414
It was so easy for you to leave.

1254
01:52:03.001 --> 01:52:06.670
Leaving you was the hardest
thing I've done in 100 years.

1255
01:52:13.470 --> 01:52:15.012
And I swear.

1256
01:52:16.348 --> 01:52:19.016
I will never fail you again.

1257
01:52:21.311 --> 01:52:22.853
I'm so sorry.

1258
01:52:25.273 --> 01:52:27.191
Charlie's coming.
Hey.

1259
01:52:30.362 --> 01:52:31.737
You okay?

1260
01:52:33.156 --> 01:52:34.406
I'm fine.

1261
01:52:37.536 --> 01:52:39.703
Dad. you don't have to worry.

1262
01:52:40.205 --> 01:52:42.206
You know. last time you
said that. you took off.

1263
01:52:42.290 --> 01:52:44.458
I didn't see you for three days.

1264
01:52:46.169 --> 01:52:48.045
I'm really sorry. Dad.

1265
01:52:49.840 --> 01:52:53.551
Bella. do not ever
do that to me again.

1266
01:52:56.388 --> 01:52:57.471
Ever.

1267
01:53:00.267 --> 01:53:01.851
And you're grounded

1268
01:53:02.310 --> 01:53:04.436
for the rest of your life.

1269
01:53:05.605 --> 01:53:06.772
Okay.

1270
01:53:17.075 --> 01:53:19.869
I'm not technically
breaking any of his rules.

1271
01:53:22.873 --> 01:53:26.083
He did say I couldn't take
a step inside the door.

1272
01:53:26.585 --> 01:53:28.878
I came in through the window.

1273
01:53:32.507 --> 01:53:35.009
He's not gonna
forgive me easily.

1274
01:53:37.470 --> 01:53:38.762
I know.

1275
01:53:40.807 --> 01:53:42.183
Can you?

1276
01:53:45.937 --> 01:53:47.521
I hope you can.

1277
01:53:48.315 --> 01:53:51.525
'cause I honestly don't know
how to live without you.

1278
01:53:55.864 --> 01:53:57.281
Come here.

1279
01:54:14.925 --> 01:54:17.885
Once Alice changes me.

1280
01:54:20.805 --> 01:54:22.973
you can't get rid of me.

1281
01:54:24.184 --> 01:54:26.477
She won't need to change you.

1282
01:54:27.103 --> 01:54:30.606
There are always ways to keep
the Volturi in the dark.

1283
01:54:32.317 --> 01:54:34.693
No. No.

1284
01:54:41.493 --> 01:54:43.494
You all know what I want.

1285
01:54:45.664 --> 01:54:48.666
And I know how much
I'm asking for.

1286
01:54:50.919 --> 01:54:54.421
The only thing that I can think of
for it to be fair is to just vote.

1287
01:54:54.506 --> 01:54:57.841
You don't know what you're talking about.
Shut up.

1288
01:54:59.469 --> 01:55:00.678
Alice?

1289
01:55:01.137 --> 01:55:03.681
I already consider
you my sister.

1290
01:55:07.477 --> 01:55:09.103
Yes.
Thank you.

1291
01:55:09.187 --> 01:55:10.688
I vote yes.

1292
01:55:12.107 --> 01:55:15.609
It would be nice to not want
to kill you all the time.

1293
01:55:17.487 --> 01:55:18.487
Hmm.

1294
01:55:18.613 --> 01:55:19.947
I'm sorry.

1295
01:55:21.866 --> 01:55:24.994
I'm really sorry to both
of you for how I've acted.

1296
01:55:25.620 --> 01:55:27.663
and I'm really grateful
that you were brave enough

1297
01:55:27.747 --> 01:55:29.873
to go and save my brother.

1298
01:55:31.376 --> 01:55:34.837
But this isn't a life I would
have chosen for myself.

1299
01:55:37.382 --> 01:55:41.051
And I wish that there'd been
someone to vote no for me.

1300
01:55:43.930 --> 01:55:45.347
So. no.

1301
01:55:46.766 --> 01:55:48.684
